1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,584
We're here today with actors
Ha Ji-won and Jang Keun-suk.

2
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:19,919
Keun-suk is someone we call AP.

3
00:00:19,986 --> 00:00:21,154
Asia's Prince.

4
00:00:21,221 --> 00:00:22,489
-AP?
-AP?

5
00:00:22,555 --> 00:00:24,190
He's the original Korean Wave star.

6
00:00:24,257 --> 00:00:26,192
-AP.
-AP. Asia's Prince.

7
00:00:26,259 --> 00:00:27,460
Asia's Prince.

8
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:30,430
I'm so grateful for that. I ended up

9
00:00:30,497 --> 00:00:34,834
with a nickname much bigger than
what I thought was ever possible.

10
00:00:34,901 --> 00:00:37,470
It wasn't that
someone called me Asia's Prince.

11
00:00:37,537 --> 00:00:41,341
-I see.
-I said it myself, so it stuck around.

12
00:00:41,408 --> 00:00:42,642
-It wasn't your fans?
-No.

13
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:45,311
I always said,
"Hello, I'm Jang Keun-suk, Asia's Prince."

14
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,547
And those words kept making the headlines,

15
00:00:47,614 --> 00:00:49,949
so people began to call me Asia's Prince.

16
00:00:50,016 --> 00:00:51,684
-So…
-I didn't know.

17
00:00:51,751 --> 00:00:55,488
It was a wonder that it came true
just because I went around saying it.

18
00:00:57,791 --> 00:00:59,626
Hello, I'm Choi Hyun-suk,
Filthy Rich Chef.

19
00:00:59,692 --> 00:01:01,828
-"Filthy Rich Chef"?
-He's serious.

20
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:03,663
-"Filthy Rich Chef"?
-"Filthy Rich Chef"?

21
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,632
That makes you seem so pathetic.

22
00:01:05,698 --> 00:01:08,001
You came up with "Filthy Rich Chef"
in that short while.

23
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:10,036
I'm so embarrassed.

24
00:01:10,103 --> 00:01:11,571
I don't care if you attack me.

25
00:01:11,638 --> 00:01:13,973
All I need is money.

26
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:16,109
NOW, MY DREAM IS
TO BE A FILTHY RICH CHEF(?)

27
00:01:16,176 --> 00:01:17,310
You're too crazy for money.

28
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:19,279
-Come on.
-You're too hot for money.

29
00:01:19,345 --> 00:01:22,148
There's something else
that Keun-suk is known for.

30
00:01:22,215 --> 00:01:24,050
Show-off Keun-suk.

31
00:01:24,117 --> 00:01:26,319
-Show-off Keun-suk.
-Hello.

32
00:01:26,386 --> 00:01:28,488
There are a few here too.

33
00:01:28,555 --> 00:01:31,524
There are many big show-offs here.

34
00:01:31,591 --> 00:01:33,726
We have Show-off Chef

35
00:01:33,793 --> 00:01:35,462
and Baby Show-off Chef.

36
00:01:35,528 --> 00:01:39,432
But Keun-suk is the original show-off guy.

37
00:01:39,499 --> 00:01:43,436
I have some evidence
to prove that he's a show-off.

38
00:01:43,503 --> 00:01:45,605
-Let's take a look.
-"Those" moments?

39
00:01:45,672 --> 00:01:47,040
This is it.

40
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:48,141
The romanticist.

41
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:50,243
"Do I have a headache
because I'm more passionate…"

42
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:51,311
Gosh.

43
00:01:51,377 --> 00:01:54,914
This is a snippet
from the old social media, Cyworld.

44
00:01:54,981 --> 00:01:57,283
"The reason why
my head hurts more than others is

45
00:01:57,350 --> 00:01:59,219
because I'm more passionate than others?"

46
00:02:00,053 --> 00:02:01,721
His collars say a lot.

47
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,424
If his collars were down,
I'd think he was in actual pain.

48
00:02:04,491 --> 00:02:06,759
-But the collars are up.
-That's significant.

49
00:02:06,826 --> 00:02:09,596
The collars make a big statement.

50
00:02:09,662 --> 00:02:11,131
Did you write this yourself?

51
00:02:11,197 --> 00:02:13,833
-I did. But that's…
-Did you upload this?

52
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,470
I wrote that I was more passionate
just to be funny.

53
00:02:17,537 --> 00:02:20,340
That was a famous copy
for a painkiller at that time.

54
00:02:20,406 --> 00:02:23,009
I did a parody of that to be funny,

55
00:02:23,076 --> 00:02:26,546
but people thought I was
seriously infatuated with myself.

56
00:02:26,613 --> 00:02:29,282
That was a witty and humorous post.

57
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:30,416
It was amusing.

58
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:32,919
-Was it? You thought highly of that.
-Yes.

59
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:36,823
Even now,
people who remember me from those days

60
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:40,727
still say that I'm a bit of a show-off.

61
00:02:40,793 --> 00:02:43,296
But I like that.

62
00:02:43,363 --> 00:02:46,966
If you can't be a show-off,
you won't have such guts to be so bold.

63
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:49,035
It'd feel like
I was living without a dream.

64
00:02:49,102 --> 00:02:51,871
I'm the type
who likes to throw big statements.

65
00:02:51,938 --> 00:02:54,073
Here's one thing I can connect with.

66
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:55,375
Because showing off

67
00:02:55,441 --> 00:02:58,811
adds a little romance
to your everyday life.

68
00:02:58,878 --> 00:03:03,449
Others will say using the words
from novels and films in real life

69
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:05,885
makes someone sound cheesy.

70
00:03:05,952 --> 00:03:09,189
But people who live that life are
serious about it.

71
00:03:09,255 --> 00:03:11,558
So those who misunderstand
will call us show-offs.

72
00:03:11,624 --> 00:03:15,962
If you think about it,
these are the romantics who live in style.

73
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:17,697
That's what I'm talking about.

74
00:03:18,264 --> 00:03:19,966
You two are big show-offs.

75
00:03:21,134 --> 00:03:24,771
-Sitting right next to each other.
-The big show-offs.

76
00:03:24,837 --> 00:03:26,806
It's such a sight to see you two together.

77
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:29,742
-The two show-offs.
-Yes.

78
00:03:29,809 --> 00:03:33,213
I was greatly moved
as I listened to them talk.

79
00:03:34,113 --> 00:03:35,882
You were greatly moved by these show-offs?

80
00:03:36,983 --> 00:03:41,120
I connected quite deeply
with the two men's outlook on life.

81
00:03:41,187 --> 00:03:43,389
-And I agree with them.
-You're a romantic.

82
00:03:43,456 --> 00:03:45,592
I need the confidence to say
that I'll become

83
00:03:45,658 --> 00:03:47,894
the best chef in this world

84
00:03:47,961 --> 00:03:49,495
to at least be the best in Korea.

85
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:51,431
-That's what I believe.
-I see.

86
00:03:51,497 --> 00:03:53,933
-Dreaming big.
-It's great to have big goals.

87
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,501
Keun-suk is such a show-off

88
00:03:56,135 --> 00:03:58,338
that he shows off
his ability to take spicy food.

89
00:03:58,404 --> 00:03:59,706
You must enjoy spicy dishes.

90
00:03:59,772 --> 00:04:02,675
I'm still not sure
what spiciness feels like.

91
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:05,144
I've never thought anything was spicy.

92
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,414
Hey, that was just showing off.

93
00:04:08,481 --> 00:04:09,949
That was bluffing.

94
00:04:10,016 --> 00:04:12,685
Look at how everyone is
missing out on romance!

95
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:15,888
If it doesn't feel spicy to you,
do you at least sweat?

96
00:04:15,955 --> 00:04:17,624
That's only because it's hot.

97
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,592
-When you eat spicy food, I mean.
-In winter.

98
00:04:19,659 --> 00:04:23,329
It does burn my stomach, though.
At times, it feels like it's too much.

99
00:04:23,396 --> 00:04:26,032
-That means it felt spicy.
-That's spiciness.

100
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:27,267
It's hard on your stomach?

101
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:30,570
-But not my mouth. I can keep eating it.
-Really?

102
00:04:30,637 --> 00:04:31,704
It's not hot in your mouth?

103
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:33,706
It feels fine in his mouth
unless his stomach

104
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:35,275
-sends him a sign, right?
-Yes.

105
00:04:35,341 --> 00:04:38,511
I want to see him get conquered.

106
00:04:38,578 --> 00:04:40,580
-What?
-He said no food feels too spicy,

107
00:04:40,647 --> 00:04:43,116
so I want to make him
feel that spiciness.

108
00:04:43,182 --> 00:04:46,019
-Make him feel that?
-Like, "This should be spicy enough"?

109
00:04:46,085 --> 00:04:50,290
Yes, I suddenly feel like
I want to make him feel it.

110
00:04:50,356 --> 00:04:54,994
Keun-suk may end up fainting
before he leaves the studio today.

111
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:57,764
Not only can he take lots of spicy food,

112
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,932
but he can take lots of alcohol too.

113
00:04:59,999 --> 00:05:03,069
We should find out
if he was just bluffing or not.

114
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,805
I wouldn't say I drink a lot,
but I do enjoy it.

115
00:05:05,872 --> 00:05:06,873
I do like to drink.

116
00:05:06,939 --> 00:05:08,608
How many drinks can you take?

117
00:05:08,675 --> 00:05:09,942
How many?

118
00:05:10,877 --> 00:05:13,513
I've never been drunk,
so I don't exactly know.

119
00:05:13,579 --> 00:05:16,683
-He's never been drunk.
-He's never been drunk.

120
00:05:16,749 --> 00:05:20,453
HE'S ON ANOTHER LEVEL OF BLUFFING,
PUTTING EVERYONE IN SHOCK

121
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,188
-You probably didn't know.
-I'd get tired for a bit

122
00:05:22,255 --> 00:05:23,489
when I drink a lot and fall asleep.

123
00:05:23,556 --> 00:05:26,392
-That's getting drunk.
-He's a show-off.

124
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:29,228
When have you had the most drinks?

125
00:05:29,295 --> 00:05:32,999
-I once had a drink with Choo Sung-hoon.
-Choo Sung-hoon.

126
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:37,003
-We had 12 bottles of wine.
-You had 12 bottles?

127
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:38,438
-What?
-Twelve bottles?

128
00:05:38,504 --> 00:05:39,872
-That's a lot.
-Just the two of you?

129
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:42,375
-The two of you?
-After we had it…

130
00:05:42,442 --> 00:05:44,410
-We were at Roppongi.
-I see.

131
00:05:44,477 --> 00:05:46,212
I said, "If you're okay,
let's have another drink."

132
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:48,548
But Sung-hoon was
already swimming on the ground.

133
00:05:48,614 --> 00:05:50,083
On the street.

134
00:05:50,149 --> 00:05:52,151
I was like, "What's going on?"

135
00:05:52,218 --> 00:05:54,087
I mean, he was Sung-hoon.

136
00:05:54,153 --> 00:05:55,321
-But you were fine.
-Yes.

137
00:05:55,388 --> 00:05:57,757
So I was a bit concerned and flustered.

138
00:05:57,824 --> 00:06:00,960
Even if they split that in half,
12 bottles mean they each had 6.

139
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,562
-Exactly.
-Six bottles each?

140
00:06:02,628 --> 00:06:04,997
Then to you, Sung-hoon is someone
who can't take his alcohol?

141
00:06:05,064 --> 00:06:07,567
-He gets easily drunk.
-Easily drunk.

142
00:06:07,633 --> 00:06:09,001
He gets drunk easily?

143
00:06:09,068 --> 00:06:11,604
He can't go around saying
he can take a lot of alcohol.

144
00:06:11,671 --> 00:06:13,639
Just to check,

145
00:06:13,706 --> 00:06:15,975
can you make a video call to Sung-hoon?

146
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,276
-Right now?
-Yes.

147
00:06:17,343 --> 00:06:21,514
-Should I give him a call?
-Let's see if he remembers that day.

148
00:06:21,581 --> 00:06:23,683
-Can Keun-suk really hold his drink?
-Right.

149
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,585
I want to know. A cross-check.

150
00:06:25,651 --> 00:06:29,389
Let's see if he remembers that day.
Can Keun-suk really hold his drink?

151
00:06:29,455 --> 00:06:30,623
Hey, Sung-hoon.

152
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:32,859
-I can see you.
-<i>Yes, I can see you.</i>

153
00:06:32,925 --> 00:06:35,595
Sung-hoon, I'm on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

154
00:06:35,661 --> 00:06:36,763
-<i>Really?</i>
-Yes.

155
00:06:36,829 --> 00:06:40,700
-Hey, Sung-hoon! It's nice to see you.
-Nice to see you.

156
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,135
In the past,

157
00:06:42,201 --> 00:06:44,470
have you had wine

158
00:06:44,537 --> 00:06:47,840
with Keun-suk in Roppongi?

159
00:06:48,441 --> 00:06:49,609
<i>I have.</i>

160
00:06:49,675 --> 00:06:51,144
He has. That was a fact.

161
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:53,012
After you two had a drink,

162
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:56,916
he said you practically
rolled around on the floor.

163
00:06:56,983 --> 00:06:58,985
-He was swimming.
-You were swimming,

164
00:06:59,051 --> 00:07:01,554
while Keun-suk was perfectly fine.
Is this true?

165
00:07:01,621 --> 00:07:03,423
-Please tell us the truth.
-This one.

166
00:07:03,489 --> 00:07:05,391
<i>Yes, all right.</i>

167
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:08,961
-<i>The two of us had so much to drink.</i>
-The two of you.

168
00:07:09,028 --> 00:07:12,865
<i>We had so much wine,</i>

169
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:16,369
<i>so it was true that I swam on the ground.</i>

170
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:19,005
-That was true.
-He did swim on the ground.

171
00:07:19,071 --> 00:07:21,073
-He wasn't bluffing.
-That was true.

172
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:22,241
-It's true.
-<i>But there was</i>

173
00:07:23,176 --> 00:07:25,878
<i>this other guy who swam next to me.</i>

174
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,014
What?

175
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:30,917
-He did it with him.
-Another guy swam next to him.

176
00:07:30,983 --> 00:07:32,552
That was Keun-suk.

177
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:36,055
-You did it together.
-They swam together.

178
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:39,592
-He said it as if he didn't do it.
-But he did.

179
00:07:39,659 --> 00:07:42,028
<i>We had fun swimming together,</i>

180
00:07:42,094 --> 00:07:43,229
<i>but we couldn't go forward.</i>

181
00:07:43,896 --> 00:07:45,231
You couldn't go forward.

182
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:48,468
-They couldn't go forward.
-They were in the same spot.

183
00:07:48,534 --> 00:07:51,571
Keun-suk claims that he was fine.

184
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:53,639
<i>No, he gets drunk much faster than I do.</i>

185
00:07:54,774 --> 00:07:57,076
-Really?
-You two tell different stories.

186
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:59,312
Did you know <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> restarted?

187
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:02,715
-<i>Yes, I knew. Please invite me.</i>
-Can you…

188
00:08:02,782 --> 00:08:04,283
You have to come.

189
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:07,386
-<i>Yes, of course. Please invite me.</i>
-Yes, sure.

190
00:08:07,453 --> 00:08:10,323
-Thanks a lot, Sung-hoon. I'll call you.
-<i>Bye.</i>

191
00:08:10,389 --> 00:08:12,325
-<i>You can't hold your drink.</i>
-Don't drink.

192
00:08:13,626 --> 00:08:15,361
-What's going on?
-Wait.

193
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:18,164
-You two swam together.
-This wasn't what you said, Keun-suk.

194
00:08:18,231 --> 00:08:22,335
-He must've dreamt while swimming.
-Sung-hoon?

195
00:08:22,401 --> 00:08:24,337
I was watching everything.

196
00:08:24,403 --> 00:08:26,506
-I think…
-Yes?

197
00:08:26,572 --> 00:08:28,741
…he just doesn't accept the truth.

198
00:08:30,243 --> 00:08:31,511
He said he was never drunk.

199
00:08:31,577 --> 00:08:33,179
Do you drink alone too?

200
00:08:33,246 --> 00:08:37,049
I've drank alone before,
but I don't do it anymore.

201
00:08:37,116 --> 00:08:39,752
I'm afraid I'll end up calling my exes.

202
00:08:40,553 --> 00:08:43,523
-It'll be odd if I text, "Are you asleep?"
-Yes, right.

203
00:08:43,589 --> 00:08:44,690
"Are you sleeping?"

204
00:08:44,757 --> 00:08:48,294
-Did you stop after making that mistake?
-You've done it.

205
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:49,862
You've done that before.

206
00:08:49,929 --> 00:08:50,963
I have.

207
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,966
That's what he does when he gets drunk.

208
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,735
I don't think that's my drunken habit.

209
00:08:55,801 --> 00:08:57,803
-Love.
-"Love"?

210
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:59,972
My unending love.

211
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:01,541
I can't mess with him.

212
00:09:01,607 --> 00:09:02,975
-Those eyes.
-Help me, Show-off Chef.

213
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:05,912
-That's his drunken habit.
-That is, right?

214
00:09:05,978 --> 00:09:08,814
-That's romance.
-Yes.

215
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:12,385
We're receiving floods of stories
about Keun-suk's bluffs.

216
00:09:12,451 --> 00:09:14,353
-More?
-Is today the Show-off Special?

217
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:17,056
After he showed off how he can take
spicy food and lots of drinks,

218
00:09:17,123 --> 00:09:19,125
he showed off his cooking skills too.

219
00:09:19,191 --> 00:09:21,360
During the preliminary interview
with our crew,

220
00:09:21,427 --> 00:09:23,563
he said, "Why all 15 minutes?
Just use 10 minutes."

221
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:28,834
"Ten minutes are enough
for me to whip up something."

222
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:32,138
-Did you say this or not?
-Is this true?

223
00:09:32,204 --> 00:09:34,407
The production crew was in shock.

224
00:09:34,473 --> 00:09:37,743
Because I like to drink, I'd make
hangover food for myself in the morning.

225
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:40,446
I can make simple dishes like pho, taco,

226
00:09:40,513 --> 00:09:44,283
or kal-guksu all under ten minutes.

227
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:46,118
-I see.
-Do you make them yourself?

228
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:50,423
I try not to eat delivery food
if I can help it.

229
00:09:50,489 --> 00:09:52,725
Chef Kang-rok, can you make
kal-guksu in ten minutes?

230
00:09:53,292 --> 00:09:55,394
-It's impossible.
-I see.

231
00:09:55,461 --> 00:09:57,663
Is he bluffing or not? Please be honest.

232
00:09:57,730 --> 00:09:59,632
I hope he admits it.

233
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:04,337
-It's time to admit it.
-It's time.

234
00:10:04,403 --> 00:10:06,539
-I realized that while I listened.
-I see.

235
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:09,642
I even heard that
Keun-suk wanted to be here as a cook.

236
00:10:09,709 --> 00:10:12,445
Is that so? My gosh.

237
00:10:12,511 --> 00:10:14,113
-Isn't that huge?
-Gosh.

238
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:17,049
If that kind of opportunity comes up,

239
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:19,785
do you really want to come and do it?

240
00:10:19,852 --> 00:10:23,322
Yes, anytime.
I want to try if you'll have me.

241
00:10:23,389 --> 00:10:25,424
If you had to do it, who would you fight?

242
00:10:25,491 --> 00:10:28,060
-I want to try fighting Poong.
-I see.

243
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:31,664
-It'll feel worthwhile to fight me.
-He's an easier fight.

244
00:10:31,731 --> 00:10:36,135
-He was nicknamed Knockoff Chef before.
-Yes, the Knockoff Chef.

245
00:10:36,202 --> 00:10:40,272
-I also use the nickname Chef Yame.
-Is that so?

246
00:10:40,339 --> 00:10:42,842
I also am an uncertified cook,

247
00:10:42,908 --> 00:10:46,212
but I also wanted it to mean
everything I cooked was yummy.

248
00:10:46,278 --> 00:10:47,480
-So I'm Chef Yame.
-I see.

249
00:10:47,546 --> 00:10:51,717
I wanted to see how the battle would go
between Knockoff Chef and Chef Yame.

250
00:10:51,784 --> 00:10:56,122
I also realized that
Ji-won had played a chef before.

251
00:10:56,188 --> 00:10:59,258
I actually went into an open kitchen

252
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,494
and pretended I wasn't Ha Ji-won

253
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:05,498
to work there as a rookie chef.

254
00:11:05,564 --> 00:11:09,735
I've begun to respect chefs even more
since that experience.

255
00:11:09,802 --> 00:11:13,572
Did you get compliments
from actual chefs who were there?

256
00:11:13,639 --> 00:11:16,108
-I was the master of tasting.
-Master of tasting.

257
00:11:17,977 --> 00:11:20,279
-She must have a good taste.
-Did they say,

258
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:21,947
-"You know when it's seasoned perfectly"?
-Yes.

259
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:25,051
We might have to escort her out
when we have five minutes.

260
00:11:25,117 --> 00:11:28,587
-We go and taste the food at five minutes.
-Yes.

261
00:11:28,654 --> 00:11:31,023
-Can you come and do that?
-Okay.

262
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:33,793
Since she's the master of tasting.

263
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:37,797
Keun-suk must've felt something else
while looking at the kitchen.

264
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:39,131
He said this to our crew.

265
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:44,303
"I've had a chilling experience
at one of the restaurants

266
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:46,439
run by one of your chefs."

267
00:11:46,505 --> 00:11:51,210
-I was very young, back when I was 20, 21.
-That's young.

268
00:11:51,277 --> 00:11:54,146
-Chef Hyun-suk…
-Chef Hyun-suk.

269
00:11:54,213 --> 00:11:57,783
It wasn't an everyday thing
to go to a fine dining restaurant, right?

270
00:11:57,850 --> 00:12:01,454
So I decided to visit out of curiosity,
wondering what it was like.

271
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:04,623
I remember that he had an open kitchen.

272
00:12:04,690 --> 00:12:07,460
And everything happened in there
seemed like a battlefield.

273
00:12:07,526 --> 00:12:09,829
-I see.
-I saw fire everywhere

274
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:12,865
and probably someone screaming,
but I couldn't really hear it.

275
00:12:12,932 --> 00:12:15,267
I thought I should eat quickly and leave.

276
00:12:15,334 --> 00:12:17,269
-You made your customer anxious!
-See?

277
00:12:17,336 --> 00:12:19,805
-How can he do that?
-Why did you do that?

278
00:12:19,872 --> 00:12:21,874
He must've slapped his staff and all.

279
00:12:21,941 --> 00:12:24,176
That's so scary! Did you spank them, too?

280
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:27,580
It must've been very bad
if he had to leave.

281
00:12:27,646 --> 00:12:30,516
Young Keun-suk thought,
"So this is a fine dining restaurant."

282
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:31,584
We need you to explain.

283
00:12:31,650 --> 00:12:33,552
Did I blurt out swear words?

284
00:12:34,186 --> 00:12:36,655
-He's not even sure.
-Chef Hyun-suk!

285
00:12:36,722 --> 00:12:38,724
-He got up and left in shock.
-I couldn't say it on TV,

286
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:41,861
but he told the production crew,
"I saw the devil himself."

287
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:43,896
-He saw the devil in the kitchen.
-The devil.

288
00:12:43,963 --> 00:12:46,065
-In the kitchen.
-Yes, I remember.

289
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:47,933
He was sitting by the window.

290
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,769
I was telling my staff,

291
00:12:49,835 --> 00:12:53,806
"Do this properly.
Do your best for your customers!"

292
00:12:53,873 --> 00:12:55,241
I said that with such passion.

293
00:12:55,307 --> 00:12:57,610
-Such passion?
-How did you do it?

294
00:12:57,676 --> 00:12:59,245
"Our customers are waiting!

295
00:12:59,311 --> 00:13:02,648
We're chefs!" That was what I said.

296
00:13:02,715 --> 00:13:04,683
You just said those very passionately.

297
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:06,418
It was a misunderstanding.

298
00:13:06,485 --> 00:13:09,221
I went to this restaurant
run by another chef.

299
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:10,856
He's very gentle, good-looking,

300
00:13:10,923 --> 00:13:13,325
-and makes pretty dishes too.
-Who was it?

301
00:13:13,392 --> 00:13:15,661
But I heard something from the kitchen.

302
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:19,632
-That's wrong.
-He was yelling in there.

303
00:13:19,698 --> 00:13:22,134
-Who is it?
-And after collaborating with him,

304
00:13:22,201 --> 00:13:25,271
-I realized he had his own style.
-He does?

305
00:13:25,337 --> 00:13:27,206
I think I know who.

306
00:13:27,273 --> 00:13:31,143
-He only looks kind on the outside.
-Even my staff just goes, "Yes, sir!"

307
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:34,280
But this guy… Gosh, I'm sorry.

308
00:13:34,346 --> 00:13:36,448
But this guy… Gosh, I'm sorry.

309
00:13:36,515 --> 00:13:37,550
WAS IT SON JONG-WON?

310
00:13:37,616 --> 00:13:38,751
It was him!

311
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:40,953
-Was it Jong-won?
-No way!

312
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:43,055
-No way. You're slandering him.
-No way.

313
00:13:43,122 --> 00:13:45,391
I'm not slandering him. That's his style.

314
00:13:45,457 --> 00:13:48,460
They repeat after everything he says.

315
00:13:49,762 --> 00:13:52,765
He'd go, "Watch <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>"
They'd go, "Yes, watch <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>"

316
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:54,967
It sounds serious
if they have to repeat after him.

317
00:13:55,034 --> 00:13:57,169
Is this true?

318
00:13:57,236 --> 00:13:59,672
It's not exactly like that.

319
00:13:59,738 --> 00:14:01,440
I think it's the most important

320
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:03,509
to communicate well with good teamwork.

321
00:14:03,576 --> 00:14:04,877
When you play soccer,

322
00:14:04,944 --> 00:14:09,281
you ask your team to pass
and let them know where you are.

323
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:11,250
Yes, we do. But we don't do that.

324
00:14:11,317 --> 00:14:13,452
When I say, "Do this!"
they don't go, "I'll do this!"

325
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:15,621
We don't do that.

326
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:18,591
"Hey, pass it here!"
They go, "I'll pass it there!"

327
00:14:18,657 --> 00:14:20,960
-They don't do that.
-It does sound odd.

328
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:25,464
Everything is noisy in the kitchen,
and there's lots to do too.

329
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:27,032
I wanted accurate communication.

330
00:14:27,099 --> 00:14:31,403
Anyway, during this conversation,
Ji-won began to look a bit grim.

331
00:14:31,470 --> 00:14:33,939
She said her ideal type was a good cook.

332
00:14:34,006 --> 00:14:35,875
-Let's ask again.
-She didn't expect this.

333
00:14:35,941 --> 00:14:37,943
Is a good cook your ideal type?

334
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:39,545
-Yes.
-Still?

335
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:45,184
I understand why chefs scream
and do these things.

336
00:14:45,251 --> 00:14:48,120
This proves the difference

337
00:14:48,187 --> 00:14:51,624
between someone who has been in a kitchen
compared to a layman.

338
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:53,759
KIM POONG'S MYSTERIOUS 1 LOSS

339
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:55,995
Before we open his fridge,

340
00:14:56,061 --> 00:14:58,664
let's find out his orders

341
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:01,166
and decide on the contenders.

342
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:03,636
Here are the orders

343
00:15:03,702 --> 00:15:06,138
from Keun-suk,
the self-proclaimed amateur cook!

344
00:15:06,205 --> 00:15:09,775
The first order is, "It's showtime!"

345
00:15:09,842 --> 00:15:12,478
I see. You used to say that often.

346
00:15:12,544 --> 00:15:14,680
-He did it as he hosted shows.
-Yes.

347
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:16,882
I say that when I feel confident.

348
00:15:16,949 --> 00:15:18,884
What kind of dishes are you looking for?

349
00:15:18,951 --> 00:15:21,654
I wanted to set no limits
and leave the chefs to do

350
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:24,857
all they could with my fridge
when I came on the show.

351
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:29,628
I wanted to see the chefs' showtime,
their ensemble, so to speak.

352
00:15:29,695 --> 00:15:31,030
-Do as you wish.
-Yes.

353
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,665
I want my ingredients

354
00:15:32,731 --> 00:15:35,467
to come out and shine
thanks to their performance.

355
00:15:35,534 --> 00:15:37,169
-That's what I want.
-A freestyle round.

356
00:15:37,236 --> 00:15:40,105
And the second order is? Let's see it.

357
00:15:40,172 --> 00:15:42,574
"I won't cry even if it's spicy."

358
00:15:42,641 --> 00:15:44,376
That's the good old leetspeak.

359
00:15:44,443 --> 00:15:46,979
-I won't cry even if it's spicy.
-He's showing off his spiciness meter.

360
00:15:47,046 --> 00:15:50,449
I love to buy different sauces
whenever I'm abroad.

361
00:15:50,516 --> 00:15:55,955
Naturally, I began to collect
different spicy sauces and condiments,

362
00:15:56,021 --> 00:15:57,022
including chili peppers.

363
00:15:57,089 --> 00:16:00,492
I want to taste something
that explodes with spiciness.

364
00:16:00,559 --> 00:16:03,028
-Gosh.
-He wants to taste that spiciness.

365
00:16:03,095 --> 00:16:06,165
He claimed he never thought
anything was spicy in his mouth.

366
00:16:06,231 --> 00:16:09,935
The chefs probably have no idea
how spicy it could be.

367
00:16:10,002 --> 00:16:11,937
There's no limit at all.

368
00:16:12,004 --> 00:16:13,305
-I see.
-Just go all out.

369
00:16:14,006 --> 00:16:18,010
I want to taste the most spicy dish
they can whip up for me.

370
00:16:18,077 --> 00:16:21,947
If you shed a tear
because it's too spicy,

371
00:16:22,014 --> 00:16:23,215
would that chef win?

372
00:16:23,282 --> 00:16:25,384
I wouldn't cry because it's too spicy.

373
00:16:25,451 --> 00:16:27,219
But I'd be too moved.

374
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:29,355
SO MOVED…

375
00:16:29,421 --> 00:16:31,123
He's so good at this.

376
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:34,793
The chefs who haven't gone yet are

377
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,395
Lee Yeon-bok, Choi Hyun-suk,

378
00:16:36,462 --> 00:16:38,664
Son Jong-won, and Kwon Sung-jun.

379
00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:40,232
Chinese cuisine is spicy, right?

380
00:16:40,299 --> 00:16:42,935
-When it comes to spicy food, yes.
-You can raise your hand first.

381
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:45,637
-Yes.
-Claim it. It's an individual battle.

382
00:16:45,704 --> 00:16:47,406
It's better to pick something quickly.

383
00:16:47,473 --> 00:16:49,942
I'll go cook for the order,
"I won't cry even if it's spicy."

384
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:53,212
-"I won't cry even if it's spicy."
-"I won't cry even if it's spicy."

385
00:16:53,278 --> 00:16:56,215
That's his specialty.

386
00:16:56,281 --> 00:16:57,383
Who'll fight him?

387
00:16:57,449 --> 00:16:59,418
And these three are left.

388
00:16:59,485 --> 00:17:01,253
-They don't do spicy food.
-They're looking around.

389
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:05,524
-It'll be tough for Western cuisine.
-Yes, it won't be easy.

390
00:17:05,591 --> 00:17:08,994
Who'll raise their hand first?
Chef Hyun-suk!

391
00:17:09,061 --> 00:17:10,996
I'll go with the showtime.

392
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:14,400
-We were talking about spicy food.
-I thought you'd pick spicy food.

393
00:17:14,466 --> 00:17:16,502
-It's not that.
-What was that?

394
00:17:16,568 --> 00:17:18,203
When he wanted "It's showtime,"

395
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:20,272
I thought he wanted to see

396
00:17:20,339 --> 00:17:23,308
the fanciest, the most impressive dish
we could make on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

397
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:25,177
Not many chefs can

398
00:17:25,244 --> 00:17:27,212
make that a reality.

399
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:29,148
That's true.

400
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:30,949
-There's one.
-There's you.

401
00:17:31,016 --> 00:17:32,584
One of them is Hyun-suk.

402
00:17:32,651 --> 00:17:37,122
-Then I'll go with showtime too.
-It's showtime!

403
00:17:37,189 --> 00:17:39,158
Sung-jun, what will you do?

404
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:41,260
Sung-jun is in trouble.

405
00:17:41,326 --> 00:17:44,963
The thing is,
I don't really notice spicy food either.

406
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:48,400
-Oh, no.
-And I've never been drunk either.

407
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:50,736
You don't drink!

408
00:17:50,803 --> 00:17:53,138
-You don't drink!
-I've never been drunk.

409
00:17:53,205 --> 00:17:54,706
You can't taste spiciness?

410
00:17:54,773 --> 00:17:56,508
I don't really notice it.

411
00:17:56,575 --> 00:17:58,677
He doesn't eat spicy food either.

412
00:17:58,744 --> 00:18:02,448
-I've now begun as a slow starter.
-Yes, you have.

413
00:18:02,514 --> 00:18:07,219
So I want to challenge myself against
the leader and the king of the show.

414
00:18:07,286 --> 00:18:08,287
COMING RIGHT UP

415
00:18:09,154 --> 00:18:11,390
-That's so sexy!
-So sexy!

416
00:18:11,457 --> 00:18:13,358
It's Jong-won's showtime!

417
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:14,726
STANDING AUTOMATICALLY

418
00:18:14,793 --> 00:18:16,829
THE PRETTIEST DISHES
IN THE HISTORY OF THE SHOW

419
00:18:17,329 --> 00:18:19,498
This is crazy.
How did he do this in 15 minutes?

420
00:18:19,565 --> 00:18:21,300
It'll be atomically spicy.

421
00:18:22,201 --> 00:18:23,669
<i>I'll make everything spicy.</i>

422
00:18:24,470 --> 00:18:26,338
-Drink some milk!
-Milk!

423
00:18:26,405 --> 00:18:27,506
FROWNING

424
00:18:27,573 --> 00:18:30,542
-He can't taste the food.
-Is it atomic?

425
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:33,545
-It's an atomic bomb!
-It's an atomic bomb!

426
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:36,115
You did it. It's done.

427
00:18:36,181 --> 00:18:38,650
-Is it spicy?
-It must be spicy.

428
00:18:38,717 --> 00:18:40,652
-He's finally feeling it.
-He feels it.

429
00:18:40,719 --> 00:18:41,720
<i>Are you crying?</i>

430
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:44,790
And now, let's take a look inside

431
00:18:44,857 --> 00:18:48,360
Asia's Prince, Keun-suk's fridge.

432
00:18:48,427 --> 00:18:51,396
That's Keun-suk's fridge, and you can
already see shelf-stable ingredients.

433
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:54,199
-You can see that he enjoys cooking.
-That's a lot.

434
00:18:54,266 --> 00:18:55,567
I was surprised too.

435
00:18:55,634 --> 00:18:58,203
The production crew took everything
the day before.

436
00:18:58,270 --> 00:19:00,205
I never knew my house was that big.

437
00:19:00,272 --> 00:19:01,807
It took up a lot of space.

438
00:19:01,874 --> 00:19:04,877
They took a huge stash
of everything I had.

439
00:19:04,943 --> 00:19:06,979
<i>-I see.</i>
<i>-Your house became bigger.</i>

440
00:19:07,045 --> 00:19:09,114
<i>It means he uses everything.</i>

441
00:19:09,181 --> 00:19:11,984
-We've never seen that many condiments.
-Right?

442
00:19:12,050 --> 00:19:13,519
Do you use this fridge alone?

443
00:19:13,585 --> 00:19:16,989
-Yes, I live alone and use it alone.
-I see.

444
00:19:17,055 --> 00:19:18,757
Let's look at the shelves first.

445
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:21,827
-That side first, the pantry.
-Wait.

446
00:19:21,894 --> 00:19:23,896
On the top shelf,

447
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:26,865
there are all kinds of spicy condiments.

448
00:19:26,932 --> 00:19:29,168
Buldak sauce.

449
00:19:29,234 --> 00:19:31,737
This one says, "Death Sauce."

450
00:19:31,803 --> 00:19:34,072
-"Death"?
-And Buldak sauce.

451
00:19:34,139 --> 00:19:35,841
This is sriracha.

452
00:19:35,908 --> 00:19:38,510
That's a version of sriracha
with a high level of chili pepper.

453
00:19:38,577 --> 00:19:39,578
GASP

454
00:19:39,645 --> 00:19:42,114
-This must be really spicy.
-Yes.

455
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:46,218
Wait, you haven't opened these.

456
00:19:46,285 --> 00:19:47,786
I guess you haven't had these.

457
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:51,156
It's because those two aren't spicy to me.

458
00:19:51,223 --> 00:19:52,658
-I see.
-What?

459
00:19:52,724 --> 00:19:55,794
-What now?
-To me, those two just taste sweet.

460
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:57,896
-I never had to use those to cook.
-It's not spicy?

461
00:19:57,963 --> 00:20:00,699
Those aren't even spicy enough. I see.

462
00:20:00,766 --> 00:20:03,969
Is this capsaicin sauce safe to use?
It's marked until February 8th, 2023.

463
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:06,171
-Did you say 2023?
-Capsaicin should be fine.

464
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:09,141
-I think it's fine if it's stored well.
-Do you?

465
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:11,109
-It's too spicy for germs to grow.
-They can't grow.

466
00:20:11,176 --> 00:20:12,611
-It can't get in.
-It's not that.

467
00:20:12,678 --> 00:20:15,147
It'll become less spicy
once it gets a bit stale.

468
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:16,682
DID HE KEEP IT
UNTIL IT BECAME SWEET?

469
00:20:16,748 --> 00:20:19,918
-It's less spicy after the use-by date.
-He's fermenting it.

470
00:20:19,985 --> 00:20:21,119
It's the same for mala oil.

471
00:20:21,186 --> 00:20:23,021
-But capsaicin sauce is spicy.
-Whoa.

472
00:20:23,088 --> 00:20:25,157
-It already smells spicy.
-Capsaicin.

473
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:27,526
Yes, it hits you hard. It's spicy.

474
00:20:27,593 --> 00:20:32,064
Let's go down a shelf.
We can find condiments he often uses.

475
00:20:32,130 --> 00:20:33,498
What's this?

476
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:36,635
-Black vinegar, used in Chinese cuisine.
-Black vinegar.

477
00:20:36,702 --> 00:20:38,570
I use it when I eat malatang.

478
00:20:38,637 --> 00:20:40,739
-It's a great sauce with that.
-It's hard to make at home.

479
00:20:40,806 --> 00:20:42,641
You can make that?
He has Sichuan pepper too.

480
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:44,676
And these are star anise.

481
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:48,213
I use it to make braised dishes
with soy sauce as the base,

482
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:51,016
-and sometimes into braised short ribs.
-It's used often for braises.

483
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,451
He has all kinds of Chinese condiments.

484
00:20:52,517 --> 00:20:55,921
-I can see that he's a good amateur cook.
-It's like an Asian supermarket.

485
00:20:55,988 --> 00:20:58,590
The sesame oil with the red cap.

486
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:01,360
-This one?
-For the last seven to eight years,

487
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:04,229
one of my fans who runs a mill

488
00:21:04,296 --> 00:21:06,365
would make and send that to me,

489
00:21:06,431 --> 00:21:09,301
-and that's the only kind I eat.
-That's amazing.

490
00:21:09,368 --> 00:21:10,869
Do you dunk rice in it?

491
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:12,738
I don't dunk it in.

492
00:21:12,804 --> 00:21:15,540
But Ji-won did that with olive oil.

493
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:19,278
It's time to explore
the inside of his fridge.

494
00:21:19,344 --> 00:21:21,446
I wonder
what kind of ingredients he'll have.

495
00:21:21,513 --> 00:21:24,316
We present Keun-suk's fridge!

496
00:21:24,383 --> 00:21:26,918
ALL EYES ARE ON THE FRIDGE

497
00:21:26,985 --> 00:21:29,855
We present Keun-suk's fridge!

498
00:21:29,921 --> 00:21:31,456
-I see.
-Whoa.

499
00:21:31,523 --> 00:21:34,393
-For now…
-It was as I expected.

500
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:36,061
Hey, wait a second.

501
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,597
I can already tell he was conscious

502
00:21:38,664 --> 00:21:41,800
-about coming on the show.
-Yes.

503
00:21:41,867 --> 00:21:44,369
-Look at these.
-He'd only need one of these.

504
00:21:44,436 --> 00:21:48,273
But there are two, four, six,
a total of eight jars.

505
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:49,741
Do you dunk rice into truffle sauce?

506
00:21:50,575 --> 00:21:52,110
Why do you keep asking that?

507
00:21:52,177 --> 00:21:54,379
-Eight jars are one too many.
-That's staged.

508
00:21:54,446 --> 00:21:55,847
What's this?

509
00:21:55,914 --> 00:21:57,082
Those are caviars.

510
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:59,217
That really isn't there to show off.

511
00:21:59,284 --> 00:22:04,256
You ordered it in a hurry for the show
and put it inside.

512
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:05,324
Isn't that the case?

513
00:22:05,390 --> 00:22:06,692
Let me explain.

514
00:22:06,758 --> 00:22:08,460
I didn't buy those.
Some people send it to me

515
00:22:08,527 --> 00:22:09,828
-in the holidays.
-A present.

516
00:22:09,895 --> 00:22:14,132
I wondered what I should do with it
and just left it in the fridge.

517
00:22:14,199 --> 00:22:16,768
-I see.
-I often just leave it there.

518
00:22:16,835 --> 00:22:19,538
Behind the truffle sauce and caviars,

519
00:22:19,604 --> 00:22:21,973
I see lots of pickled vegetables.

520
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:26,211
-Pickled vegetables?
-These must be his staple instead.

521
00:22:26,278 --> 00:22:28,180
He likes pickled vegetables,

522
00:22:28,246 --> 00:22:32,250
but he left truffle sauce and caviar
in the front as a show.

523
00:22:32,317 --> 00:22:34,486
He's into this kind of food.

524
00:22:34,553 --> 00:22:37,122
-Do you like Korean cuisine? You do.
-I do.

525
00:22:37,189 --> 00:22:38,256
Look at that.

526
00:22:39,391 --> 00:22:41,526
-I've never seen a fridge like this.
-What's this?

527
00:22:41,593 --> 00:22:43,829
-I've never seen anything like it.
-That's neat.

528
00:22:43,895 --> 00:22:46,765
Look at how he stores his side dishes.

529
00:22:46,832 --> 00:22:49,034
-It's like a palette.
-Gosh.

530
00:22:49,101 --> 00:22:50,969
I don't like to eat those
out of their containers.

531
00:22:51,036 --> 00:22:54,339
But it takes a lot of effort
to open up every single container,

532
00:22:54,406 --> 00:22:57,709
so I decided to put some in here
and eat it out of this.

533
00:22:57,776 --> 00:23:00,112
-This is a great idea.
-He eats it like this.

534
00:23:00,178 --> 00:23:01,880
He has more pickled radish.

535
00:23:01,947 --> 00:23:04,483
He must like pickled radish.

536
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:07,219
I feel anxious when I run out of them.

537
00:23:07,285 --> 00:23:09,588
I do like kimchi,

538
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:12,691
but because I eat
lots of red and spicy food,

539
00:23:12,758 --> 00:23:15,060
the sweetness of the radish
helps with the flavor.

540
00:23:15,127 --> 00:23:17,129
-Yes, it's refreshing.
-The sweet taste.

541
00:23:17,195 --> 00:23:19,698
I enjoy pickled radish
whenever I eat spicy food.

542
00:23:19,765 --> 00:23:20,999
So pickled radish over truffle, right?

543
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:22,401
I GOT YOU, MAN

544
00:23:23,602 --> 00:23:25,003
I got you.

545
00:23:26,271 --> 00:23:27,706
What's this?

546
00:23:27,773 --> 00:23:30,442
I always make sure I don't run out of it.
It's couscous salad.

547
00:23:30,509 --> 00:23:31,676
Couscous?

548
00:23:31,743 --> 00:23:33,078
-I see.
-Do you like it?

549
00:23:33,145 --> 00:23:35,180
I nibble on it
when I feel snacky at night.

550
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:36,314
Did you buy this? Or…

551
00:23:36,381 --> 00:23:38,116
-I made it. Yes.
-Yourself?

552
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:41,253
I ran out of cumin at that time,

553
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:43,488
so I used lamb skewer seasoning instead.

554
00:23:43,555 --> 00:23:44,756
-That sounds good.
-It does.

555
00:23:44,823 --> 00:23:47,025
I use couscous often too.

556
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:50,595
And there are other ways to cook those
other than what he usually does,

557
00:23:50,662 --> 00:23:52,697
so I'm thinking of making use of that.

558
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:53,999
LOOK FORWARD TO IT

559
00:23:54,065 --> 00:23:56,535
This one looks like some sauce.

560
00:23:56,601 --> 00:24:00,038
-It's Singapore chili crab sauce.
-Chili crab.

561
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:02,574
I was watching a documentary
on chili crabs

562
00:24:02,641 --> 00:24:04,943
and craved it so much
that I decided to have some.

563
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:08,647
So I found this sauce
that I could get delivered at home,

564
00:24:08,713 --> 00:24:11,149
but I didn't want it by the next day.

565
00:24:11,216 --> 00:24:13,218
-That happens.
-I'm at halt from there.

566
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:15,387
The sauce is now just floating around.

567
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:18,423
-That's new.
-He has fish roes.

568
00:24:18,490 --> 00:24:19,624
Fish roes.

569
00:24:19,691 --> 00:24:20,759
Whoa!

570
00:24:20,826 --> 00:24:24,663
-This is the spicy shelf.
-He has lots of chili peppers.

571
00:24:24,729 --> 00:24:26,832
This is the spicy shelf.

572
00:24:26,898 --> 00:24:29,267
Cheongyang pepper, red pepper,

573
00:24:29,334 --> 00:24:31,570
and Thai chili. These are spicy.

574
00:24:31,636 --> 00:24:32,938
WIGGLING

575
00:24:33,004 --> 00:24:34,406
What are you doing?

576
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:35,474
These are spicy.

577
00:24:35,540 --> 00:24:38,076
You're good with spicy food.
Do you eat it as is?

578
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:39,845
I eat it like a snack.

579
00:24:41,279 --> 00:24:42,747
-You're that good?
-Just raw?

580
00:24:42,814 --> 00:24:45,016
-Keun-suk, show us.
-Yes, show us.

581
00:24:45,083 --> 00:24:47,285
You said you didn't think
anything was spicy.

582
00:24:47,352 --> 00:24:49,454
-Yes, this one.
-It must be spicy.

583
00:24:49,521 --> 00:24:51,289
You can't even touch your eyes
after touching these.

584
00:24:51,356 --> 00:24:53,124
-How can he eat it like a snack?
-Do I just eat it?

585
00:24:53,191 --> 00:24:56,061
-Yes, eat it like a snack.
-I do this often.

586
00:24:56,127 --> 00:24:57,829
You really eat this as a snack?

587
00:24:57,896 --> 00:24:59,598
GASPING

588
00:25:00,966 --> 00:25:03,635
-It's sweet.
-It is?

589
00:25:03,702 --> 00:25:05,036
Someone else has to try it too.

590
00:25:05,103 --> 00:25:06,638
Maybe it's really sweet.

591
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:10,642
-Chef Yeon-bok is up.
-We have to check it.

592
00:25:10,709 --> 00:25:11,943
-Do you feel okay?
-I'm fine.

593
00:25:12,010 --> 00:25:13,311
It doesn't smell too spicy.

594
00:25:13,378 --> 00:25:15,380
-Your eyes are red. Are you okay?
-I'm fine.

595
00:25:15,447 --> 00:25:18,083
-Your eyes are wet.
-His eyes are in tears.

596
00:25:18,683 --> 00:25:20,018
A BOLD ATTEMPT
AFTER KEUN-SUK'S REVIEW!

597
00:25:20,085 --> 00:25:21,152
-He says he's sweet.
-His eyes.

598
00:25:21,219 --> 00:25:22,521
-Chef Yeon-bok.
-Is it spicy?

599
00:25:23,522 --> 00:25:25,657
-I guess it's not.
-I guess it's not spicy.

600
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:28,059
-I guess it's not.
-I guess it's not spicy.

601
00:25:28,126 --> 00:25:29,661
He's feeling it.

602
00:25:29,728 --> 00:25:30,962
Whoa!

603
00:25:31,029 --> 00:25:33,732
It's hitting him!

604
00:25:33,798 --> 00:25:36,401
It just hit Chef Yeon-bok!

605
00:25:36,468 --> 00:25:37,669
He spits out everything.

606
00:25:37,736 --> 00:25:39,471
Man, I'm in trouble.

607
00:25:39,538 --> 00:25:41,806
-It smells spicy.
-This is…

608
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:43,675
-I'm really fine.
-He looks fine.

609
00:25:43,742 --> 00:25:45,777
-He looks the same way.
-He looks even more awake.

610
00:25:46,645 --> 00:25:49,514
-Are you cooling your tongue?
-He's sticking his tongue out.

611
00:25:49,581 --> 00:25:50,949
I was embarrassed.

612
00:25:52,217 --> 00:25:54,719
-You felt embarrassed?
-Chef Yeon-bok, how spicy was it?

613
00:25:54,786 --> 00:25:56,054
GARGLING HIS MOUTH
FOR THE 50TH TIME

614
00:25:56,121 --> 00:25:58,657
Chinese cuisine has lots of spicy dishes.

615
00:25:58,723 --> 00:26:02,160
-He had the whole thing.
-I already knew this was spicy.

616
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:05,230
-He said it was sweet and enjoyed it.
-Exactly.

617
00:26:05,297 --> 00:26:07,566
-It's really spicy.
-It is?

618
00:26:07,632 --> 00:26:09,501
Yes, I didn't even chew it all the way.

619
00:26:10,201 --> 00:26:11,202
That's amazing.

620
00:26:11,269 --> 00:26:13,204
It'd be amazing even if he was

621
00:26:13,271 --> 00:26:14,506
-holding himself back.
-Wait.

622
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:17,842
-The whites of your eyes are turning red.
-Stop it.

623
00:26:17,909 --> 00:26:20,478
The whites of his eyes are
starting to turn red.

624
00:26:20,545 --> 00:26:22,213
The studio's too dry.

625
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:25,750
-Really? He's driving me crazy.
-Yes.

626
00:26:25,817 --> 00:26:28,219
Sung-ju, then just have one bite.

627
00:26:28,286 --> 00:26:30,021
-Okay.
-Really?

628
00:26:30,622 --> 00:26:33,658
Chef Yeon-bok, it seemed like
you were acting for the show's sake.

629
00:26:33,725 --> 00:26:34,926
-It's spicy.
-Open up.

630
00:26:34,993 --> 00:26:37,295
PUSHING IT IN

631
00:26:37,829 --> 00:26:39,631
-You should eat that much.
-Stop pushing it in.

632
00:26:39,698 --> 00:26:40,699
Be careful!

633
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:42,334
Try just half.

634
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:45,203
-You like refreshing and spicy food.
-No, that's too spicy!

635
00:26:45,937 --> 00:26:47,606
-That's a disaster.
-His neck…

636
00:26:47,672 --> 00:26:50,709
-He's not chewing it. You have to!
-I don't think he can.

637
00:26:50,775 --> 00:26:51,776
It's sweet.

638
00:26:51,843 --> 00:26:53,411
You have to use these to cook,
so we'll stop.

639
00:26:53,478 --> 00:26:55,180
COVERING MOUTH

640
00:26:55,246 --> 00:26:56,781
Chew it. How is it?

641
00:26:56,848 --> 00:26:59,818
I just felt the juice
when I took one bite.

642
00:26:59,884 --> 00:27:02,087
It's already spicy like this.

643
00:27:02,153 --> 00:27:04,422
-Really?
-I'll be done if I chew this.

644
00:27:04,489 --> 00:27:06,524
-But you like spicy food.
-I took

645
00:27:06,591 --> 00:27:07,959
one bite, and the juice…

646
00:27:09,694 --> 00:27:11,997
THE SPICINESS FINALLY HITS HIM

647
00:27:12,063 --> 00:27:14,733
-Man!
-You're amazing.

648
00:27:14,799 --> 00:27:16,067
Whoa!

649
00:27:16,134 --> 00:27:19,270
This corner of my mouth is burning.

650
00:27:19,971 --> 00:27:23,141
So your dish should be
even spicier than this?

651
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:25,877
Even if it was spicier,
I won't notice it anyway.

652
00:27:25,944 --> 00:27:27,646
They can cook as they wish.

653
00:27:27,712 --> 00:27:29,014
Look at that big show-off.

654
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:31,116
-You'd die if it was any spicier.
-Yes.

655
00:27:31,182 --> 00:27:34,586
-You'd die.
-How will you taste the food?

656
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:36,521
What will you do?

657
00:27:36,588 --> 00:27:39,257
-Keun-suk is beyond your imagination.
-That's amazing.

658
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:40,458
Meat.

659
00:27:40,525 --> 00:27:42,794
I'm seeing lots of red meat.

660
00:27:42,861 --> 00:27:44,863
I'm a total carnivore.

661
00:27:44,929 --> 00:27:47,265
-I see.
-I'm so blatantly into meat

662
00:27:47,332 --> 00:27:51,536
that I make sure
I never run out of it in my fridge.

663
00:27:51,603 --> 00:27:54,706
That was all for Keun-suk's fridge.

664
00:27:54,773 --> 00:27:57,242
Let us begin the cook-off!

665
00:27:59,944 --> 00:28:04,349
We're about to begin the first round
with the ingredients

666
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:06,651
from Asia's Prince, Keun-suk's fridge.

667
00:28:06,718 --> 00:28:11,423
Up first is Chef Son Jong-won,
the prince of the fine dining industry.

668
00:28:11,489 --> 00:28:14,492
Up against him is Choi Hyun-suk,

669
00:28:14,559 --> 00:28:17,929
the old prince
of the fine dining industry.

670
00:28:17,996 --> 00:28:21,666
-Don't bite your lips like that.
-Come on.

671
00:28:21,733 --> 00:28:23,768
I wasn't offended. I was having fun.

672
00:28:23,835 --> 00:28:24,903
That is so, right?

673
00:28:24,969 --> 00:28:26,071
All right.

674
00:28:26,137 --> 00:28:27,305
In the new season

675
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:30,208
of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>, Chef Hyun-suk

676
00:28:30,275 --> 00:28:31,943
has not had any losses.

677
00:28:32,010 --> 00:28:35,480
Who will stop him from this rampage?

678
00:28:35,547 --> 00:28:39,184
Many are expecting
Chef Jong-won to do just that.

679
00:28:39,250 --> 00:28:42,687
There was something Chef Hyun-suk
officially said to our production crew.

680
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:45,857
"This is the biggest match
you'll ever get to see

681
00:28:45,924 --> 00:28:48,226
-here on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>."
-Gosh.

682
00:28:48,293 --> 00:28:49,594
He said that himself

683
00:28:49,661 --> 00:28:52,063
-to the production crew.
-We usually say that for him.

684
00:28:52,130 --> 00:28:53,865
It's because of our specialty,

685
00:28:53,932 --> 00:28:57,035
and the ingredients
the fridge owner has today,

686
00:28:57,102 --> 00:29:01,206
because they can be used to show
the height of fine dining.

687
00:29:01,272 --> 00:29:03,308
It'll be a game to remember.

688
00:29:03,374 --> 00:29:07,545
It feels like two masters are
up against each other.

689
00:29:07,612 --> 00:29:09,447
Two swordsmen, two assassins.

690
00:29:09,514 --> 00:29:10,715
A BATTLE UNTIL THE BEST MAN WINS?

691
00:29:10,782 --> 00:29:12,951
It's like a battle between two swordsmen.

692
00:29:13,017 --> 00:29:16,121
That's why I also want to share
a word of caution with the hosts.

693
00:29:16,187 --> 00:29:18,556
-We have to be careful?
-You said we were like swordsmen.

694
00:29:18,623 --> 00:29:21,626
When two expert swordsmen are
up against each other,

695
00:29:21,693 --> 00:29:25,096
any laymen who get into the fight
can become destroyed like dust.

696
00:29:25,163 --> 00:29:26,998
Why are you scaring us?

697
00:29:27,065 --> 00:29:30,535
I don't want you to get involved and hurt

698
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:33,338
when you're here
for the five-minute interim check.

699
00:29:33,404 --> 00:29:36,007
-In that case, we can retaliate.
-How?

700
00:29:36,074 --> 00:29:37,642
Let's go out together.

701
00:29:37,709 --> 00:29:39,244
-The two of us?
-Yes.

702
00:29:39,310 --> 00:29:43,081
-Why did you ruin the ingredient?
-I don't think you can do this.

703
00:29:43,148 --> 00:29:44,749
I respectfully apologize.

704
00:29:45,416 --> 00:29:46,818
We'll both go out.

705
00:29:46,885 --> 00:29:49,154
We can destroy you one-to-one.

706
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:50,889
We can turn a sweet dish into a salty one.

707
00:29:51,756 --> 00:29:55,593
-We have a big role to help you out.
-Yes.

708
00:29:55,660 --> 00:29:57,729
May I make this request?

709
00:29:57,796 --> 00:30:00,231
It doesn't matter what you do,

710
00:30:00,298 --> 00:30:03,835
but I want to see them put in
everything they have into this.

711
00:30:03,902 --> 00:30:05,203
THE TWO CHEFS' SHOW
IS COMING RIGHT UP

712
00:30:05,270 --> 00:30:07,272
Chef Jong-won, if you don't show

713
00:30:07,338 --> 00:30:10,208
as good a performance as Chef Hyun-suk,

714
00:30:10,275 --> 00:30:12,877
you may end up at a disadvantage
in the end.

715
00:30:12,944 --> 00:30:17,882
This is the third time
I get to cook here on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

716
00:30:17,949 --> 00:30:22,520
<i>I got nervous, and my hand trembled</i>
<i>during the first two rounds.</i>

717
00:30:22,587 --> 00:30:24,856
<i>-Yes.</i>
<i>-I felt awkward too.</i>

718
00:30:24,923 --> 00:30:28,993
But it felt more familiar
as I traveled to the studio today.

719
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:30,595
-I see.
-He adapted.

720
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:34,833
-So I'll show everything I can do today.
-He adapted.

721
00:30:34,899 --> 00:30:36,801
-There's one more thing to look for.
-What is it?

722
00:30:36,868 --> 00:30:39,537
My Sylvia is with Chef Hyun-suk.

723
00:30:39,604 --> 00:30:41,472
<i>-Yes.</i>
<i>-Will you use Sylvia?</i>

724
00:30:41,539 --> 00:30:43,408
<i>It's the cursed frying pan!</i>

725
00:30:44,442 --> 00:30:48,112
<i>Everyone who used Sylvia</i>
<i>has suffered a loss.</i>

726
00:30:48,913 --> 00:30:51,349
<i>Sylvia still doesn't have a star.</i>

727
00:30:51,416 --> 00:30:54,319
I'll throw that out if I lose today.

728
00:30:54,385 --> 00:30:56,187
SYLVIA WAS ABANDONED
AFTER SAM KIM VS KIM POONG

729
00:30:56,254 --> 00:30:57,722
What will happen to Sylvia?

730
00:30:57,789 --> 00:31:00,792
Sylvia is now the symbol of a curse,

731
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:02,560
but I'll change it into a lucky pan.

732
00:31:02,627 --> 00:31:06,731
-That's Hyun-suk.
-Will he be able to do it?

733
00:31:06,798 --> 00:31:07,799
Are you sure?

734
00:31:07,866 --> 00:31:08,867
I'm a chef.

735
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:12,437
I see. Stop opening your eyes like that.

736
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:15,506
You're so cool!

737
00:31:16,274 --> 00:31:17,275
That's my type!

738
00:31:17,342 --> 00:31:19,944
If he wants to use it, he'll use it.

739
00:31:20,011 --> 00:31:21,145
It doesn't matter what he uses.

740
00:31:21,212 --> 00:31:23,348
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS: SIRLOIN,
TRUFFLE CREAM CHEESE, CHEDDAR CHEESE

741
00:31:23,414 --> 00:31:25,550
SOY SAUCE MARINATED CRAB, BOTTARGA,
WASABI, CAVIAR, SALMON ROE, AND MORE

742
00:31:25,617 --> 00:31:27,852
My dish is called

743
00:31:27,919 --> 00:31:29,454
Roe Trio.

744
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:30,922
-Roe Trio?
-Yes.

745
00:31:30,989 --> 00:31:32,557
I'll top steak with caviar,

746
00:31:32,624 --> 00:31:35,660
bottarga, mullet roe, on pasta,

747
00:31:35,727 --> 00:31:39,163
and salmon roe on delicious rice.

748
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:41,032
-Whoa.
-I'll use three different fish roes

749
00:31:41,099 --> 00:31:44,135
with different textures and flavors,

750
00:31:44,202 --> 00:31:48,039
a perfect main dish
for a fine dining experience.

751
00:31:48,106 --> 00:31:50,041
Gosh, Roe Trio.

752
00:31:50,108 --> 00:31:51,876
-You'll make 3 dishes?
-In 15 minutes?

753
00:31:51,943 --> 00:31:53,745
Pasta, rice, and steak.

754
00:31:53,811 --> 00:31:55,647
And with the pasta…

755
00:31:55,713 --> 00:31:57,582
-No way.
-I did see pasta here,

756
00:31:57,649 --> 00:32:00,051
but his order was, "It's showtime!"

757
00:32:00,118 --> 00:32:03,121
There's a flavor I'm after,
so I'll make fresh pasta.

758
00:32:03,187 --> 00:32:04,989
SURPRISED!

759
00:32:05,056 --> 00:32:07,558
Three dishes, and he'll make fresh pasta?

760
00:32:07,625 --> 00:32:10,061
Hyun-suk is about to put on a show.

761
00:32:10,128 --> 00:32:12,997
-That's some show.
-Roe Trio.

762
00:32:13,064 --> 00:32:14,933
CHEF JONG-WON'S INGREDIENTS:
MUSTARD RELISH, TENDERLOIN, OLIVE OIL

763
00:32:14,999 --> 00:32:17,001
BOTTARGA, MAYONNAISE, PICKLED RADISH,
GROUND PEPPER WITH YUJA, AND MORE

764
00:32:17,068 --> 00:32:20,838
I prepared a dish most suitable
for the class of Asia's Prince.

765
00:32:20,905 --> 00:32:23,141
It's called Caviar Prince.

766
00:32:23,207 --> 00:32:24,742
-Caviar Prince.
-Caviar Prince.

767
00:32:24,809 --> 00:32:27,912
He had caviar he received as a present.

768
00:32:27,979 --> 00:32:29,380
I'm going to make beef tartare

769
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:32,350
with ground pepper with yuja
and your favorite, pickled radish.

770
00:32:32,417 --> 00:32:34,218
-Pickled radish.
-He likes that.

771
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:35,987
And I'll wrap it with avocado.

772
00:32:36,054 --> 00:32:39,257
He had three different types of caviar,

773
00:32:39,324 --> 00:32:41,859
so he'd be able to taste
three different flavors

774
00:32:41,926 --> 00:32:43,161
in the dish I'm making.

775
00:32:43,227 --> 00:32:44,696
I won't use any heat today.

776
00:32:44,762 --> 00:32:46,698
-You won't use heat?
-No.

777
00:32:46,764 --> 00:32:48,366
-He doesn't have a pan.
-He doesn't.

778
00:32:48,433 --> 00:32:53,604
If you won't use any heat,
it means you won't grill or fry anything.

779
00:32:53,671 --> 00:32:55,440
-I won't use any heat.
-Whoa.

780
00:32:55,506 --> 00:32:58,042
So you can win against Chef Hyun-suk
without any heat?

781
00:32:58,109 --> 00:33:00,345
IT'S THE TEASING SHOWTIME!

782
00:33:00,411 --> 00:33:03,481
That's the headline for our press release.

783
00:33:03,548 --> 00:33:06,417
"Son Jong-won Wins Against Choi Hyun-suk
Without Using Heat."

784
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:08,086
I finally get how the show progresses.

785
00:33:09,187 --> 00:33:10,888
So you won't use any heat?

786
00:33:10,955 --> 00:33:14,325
We won't let you use it
even if you ask us in the middle.

787
00:33:14,392 --> 00:33:16,661
-But I'll use the oven.
-Only the oven.

788
00:33:16,728 --> 00:33:19,430
I feel like I'm watching a movie.

789
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:22,834
This is the biggest match yet.

790
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:25,269
Let us begin the round "It's showtime"

791
00:33:25,336 --> 00:33:28,239
with ingredients from Keun-suk's fridge.

792
00:33:28,873 --> 00:33:31,109
This dignified and feel-good chef will

793
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:33,478
put on a show with good vibes.

794
00:33:33,544 --> 00:33:36,714
The Michelin prince, Chef Son Jong-won.

795
00:33:36,781 --> 00:33:40,718
He's up against this chef who'll put on
a spectacular and fantastic show,

796
00:33:40,785 --> 00:33:45,056
the king of fine dining,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

797
00:33:45,123 --> 00:33:49,694
Which one of the two shows
will capture Keun-suk's palate?

798
00:33:49,761 --> 00:33:53,765
Let us begin the 15-minute cook-off!

799
00:33:53,831 --> 00:33:55,500
The 15-minute cook-off!

800
00:34:01,506 --> 00:34:04,876
THE PRESTIGE OF THE ORIGINAL

801
00:34:05,543 --> 00:34:08,012
THE COOK-OFF BEGINS

802
00:34:09,213 --> 00:34:10,948
The show begins!

803
00:34:11,516 --> 00:34:13,017
Their 15-minute show.

804
00:34:13,718 --> 00:34:17,321
-I can't believe it. Is this a dream?
-Hyun-suk and Jong-won's show begins.

805
00:34:17,889 --> 00:34:20,491
Chef Hyun-suk will make three dishes

806
00:34:20,558 --> 00:34:23,061
-and Chef Jong-won won't use heat.
-Right.

807
00:34:23,127 --> 00:34:24,629
He pulled out steak.

808
00:34:25,196 --> 00:34:27,498
1. MAKE CUTS IN SIRLOIN
AND SEASON WITH SALT AND PEPPER

809
00:34:27,565 --> 00:34:29,901
-He's making cuts.
-Cuts.

810
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:35,139
-Chef Hyun-suk is famous for his steaks.
-Of course.

811
00:34:36,674 --> 00:34:39,944
-He'll top that with fish roe.
-He said caviar.

812
00:34:40,011 --> 00:34:41,112
Caviar.

813
00:34:41,879 --> 00:34:46,717
Jong-won is cutting some bread right now.

814
00:34:47,452 --> 00:34:49,153
1. CUT CRUSTS OFF THE BREAD
AND FLATTEN

815
00:34:49,220 --> 00:34:51,222
He's flattening bread with a rolling pin.

816
00:34:52,390 --> 00:34:55,126
HE USES A COOKIE CUTTER

817
00:34:55,193 --> 00:34:57,995
Is Chef Jong-won cutting them into shapes?

818
00:34:58,062 --> 00:35:00,064
He's punching it out.

819
00:35:00,131 --> 00:35:02,033
He's making it look pretty.

820
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:04,402
So he's using those shapes, right?

821
00:35:04,469 --> 00:35:09,407
He'll probably use that
as the shell for the tartare.

822
00:35:09,474 --> 00:35:12,276
He's showing delicate skills.

823
00:35:13,144 --> 00:35:16,013
This is Chef Jong-won,

824
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:18,449
who studied in San Francisco.

825
00:35:18,516 --> 00:35:21,018
Look at how delicate he is.

826
00:35:21,085 --> 00:35:23,654
Chef Jong-won is doing delicate work.

827
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:25,456
Don't they look like cosmos flowers?

828
00:35:25,523 --> 00:35:27,258
-They're so pretty.
-Yes.

829
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:29,994
MAKING FRESH PASTA DOUGH

830
00:35:30,061 --> 00:35:31,395
He's making the dough.

831
00:35:31,462 --> 00:35:33,397
Chef Hyun-suk is making the dough.

832
00:35:33,464 --> 00:35:36,267
-He's making fresh pasta himself.
-Wow.

833
00:35:36,868 --> 00:35:38,903
-He's doing that without measuring?
-Yes.

834
00:35:40,104 --> 00:35:42,140
HE'S THE KING
OF THE FINE DINING INDUSTRY

835
00:35:42,707 --> 00:35:44,108
HOW DOES THE DOUGH LOOK?

836
00:35:44,175 --> 00:35:45,543
He has the dough.

837
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:47,478
The texture looks perfect.

838
00:35:48,546 --> 00:35:49,947
-Nice.
-The texture's perfect.

839
00:35:50,014 --> 00:35:52,150
It's different from that udon.

840
00:35:52,216 --> 00:35:53,851
<i>Su-Su-Su-Super Udon</i>

841
00:35:53,918 --> 00:35:55,887
It came out perfectly right away.

842
00:35:55,953 --> 00:35:58,956
-What's Sylvia up to?
-It's boiling water.

843
00:35:59,023 --> 00:36:00,458
It's boiling water?

844
00:36:00,525 --> 00:36:02,560
Are you just going to boil water
and not use it?

845
00:36:03,594 --> 00:36:05,229
Even I can use it like that.

846
00:36:05,296 --> 00:36:06,998
We can do that too.

847
00:36:07,064 --> 00:36:08,566
I can use it to boil water.

848
00:36:08,633 --> 00:36:11,202
Is he using that as a humidifier?

849
00:36:11,269 --> 00:36:12,403
It is dry in here.

850
00:36:12,470 --> 00:36:14,906
-A humidifier?
-It's dry in the studio.

851
00:36:14,972 --> 00:36:17,308
-No way.
-Are you using it as a humidifier?

852
00:36:17,375 --> 00:36:18,809
Will you make it look stupid?

853
00:36:18,876 --> 00:36:20,611
Are you using it as a humidifier?

854
00:36:20,678 --> 00:36:22,280
He'll probably use it only to boil pasta.

855
00:36:22,346 --> 00:36:25,249
Really? Just to boil pasta?

856
00:36:25,316 --> 00:36:27,585
You're only saying you'll use it.

857
00:36:27,652 --> 00:36:29,854
Is this why you're using that?

858
00:36:30,421 --> 00:36:32,423
AS ALWAYS,
HE CLEANS UP RIGHT AWAY

859
00:36:33,257 --> 00:36:36,027
HE USES HIS PET TOWEL(?)

860
00:36:36,093 --> 00:36:40,131
TO PULL OUT MELTED BUTTER

861
00:36:42,233 --> 00:36:44,902
He's doing detailed work right now.

862
00:36:44,969 --> 00:36:46,804
2. BUTTER THE BREAD FLOWERS
AND PUT IT ON A TART MOLD

863
00:36:47,371 --> 00:36:50,675
Everything is so detailed.

864
00:36:51,542 --> 00:36:53,778
I can't believe he did that with bread.

865
00:36:53,844 --> 00:36:54,845
Four flowers.

866
00:36:54,912 --> 00:36:58,249
Chef Jong-won became much faster
after a few experiences.

867
00:36:58,316 --> 00:37:02,286
-He's now quick enough and not trembling.
-He is.

868
00:37:02,853 --> 00:37:04,889
STRAIGHT INTO THE OVEN

869
00:37:04,956 --> 00:37:08,092
-Will he bake those?
-He's baking those.

870
00:37:08,159 --> 00:37:10,294
He'll probably make them look like tarts.

871
00:37:10,361 --> 00:37:11,696
Tarts? I see.

872
00:37:11,762 --> 00:37:14,498
He's using a timer too.

873
00:37:15,132 --> 00:37:18,069
Chef Jong-won gets an avocado.

874
00:37:18,135 --> 00:37:20,037
-He should be careful.
-Yes.

875
00:37:20,104 --> 00:37:21,839
OPENS EASILY

876
00:37:22,373 --> 00:37:24,475
He puts a bit of lime juice on it.

877
00:37:26,477 --> 00:37:29,513
He's going to use an avocado.

878
00:37:29,580 --> 00:37:33,784
-Everything he does is very delicate.
-You're right.

879
00:37:33,851 --> 00:37:36,554
And that kind of work
makes your hands tremble.

880
00:37:36,621 --> 00:37:38,489
But he's fine today.

881
00:37:38,556 --> 00:37:42,393
He has adapted quite a lot
by his third time on the show.

882
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:45,029
HE BEGINS TO MAKE STEAK SAUCE

883
00:37:45,596 --> 00:37:47,798
4. MELT TRUFFLE CREAM CHEESE
AND CHEDDAR

884
00:37:47,865 --> 00:37:50,434
TO MAKE CHEESE SAUCE

885
00:37:51,002 --> 00:37:53,104
THE DOUGH REAPPEARS
AFTER SITTING

886
00:37:53,170 --> 00:37:54,238
Whoa.

887
00:37:54,305 --> 00:37:56,641
It really turned into dough.

888
00:37:56,707 --> 00:38:00,177
He's flattening the dough
with a rolling pin,

889
00:38:00,244 --> 00:38:01,912
probably to make pasta.

890
00:38:02,747 --> 00:38:06,417
HE SUCCESSFULLY MADE
FRESH PASTA DOUGH

891
00:38:07,084 --> 00:38:10,921
BUT HE HAS FORGOTTEN
ABOUT THE STEAK

892
00:38:10,988 --> 00:38:12,890
It's getting too smoky.

893
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:16,394
-Isn't the steak burning?
-I think it's burning.

894
00:38:16,460 --> 00:38:17,461
The steak is burning.

895
00:38:17,528 --> 00:38:18,562
Is it okay?

896
00:38:18,629 --> 00:38:20,431
See? It would've been trouble
if I didn't mention it.

897
00:38:20,498 --> 00:38:21,499
-No.
-Shh.

898
00:38:21,565 --> 00:38:23,401
SHH(?)

899
00:38:23,467 --> 00:38:26,203
-He's perfect.
-He says he's fine.

900
00:38:26,270 --> 00:38:28,139
What's wrong, Nam-no?

901
00:38:28,205 --> 00:38:31,909
-That was so chill, like hip-hop.
-That was chill like hip-hop.

902
00:38:33,444 --> 00:38:35,746
REMOVES THE KNIFE

903
00:38:36,314 --> 00:38:38,082
HE PUTS THE DOUGH
ON THE CUTTING BOARD

904
00:38:39,684 --> 00:38:41,519
Where's my knife?

905
00:38:41,585 --> 00:38:43,421
-Where's my knife?
-Your knife?

906
00:38:43,487 --> 00:38:45,323
-Where's my knife?
-Your knife?

907
00:38:45,389 --> 00:38:47,858
-Is that lemon? Lime?
-Where's my knife?

908
00:38:47,925 --> 00:38:49,093
Your knife?

909
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:51,495
-My knife.
-Your knife?

910
00:38:51,562 --> 00:38:52,930
-What are you looking for?
-His knife.

911
00:38:52,997 --> 00:38:54,532
Your knife is missing?

912
00:38:54,598 --> 00:38:56,200
-Where's my knife?
-What?

913
00:38:56,267 --> 00:38:57,335
-What is it?
-His knife.

914
00:38:57,401 --> 00:39:00,304
-You're running out of time!
-His knife is gone.

915
00:39:00,371 --> 00:39:03,441
-Hyun-suk looks flustered.
-He had his knife before.

916
00:39:03,507 --> 00:39:05,343
They can help him look for his knife.

917
00:39:05,409 --> 00:39:07,078
-Hyun-suk looks flustered.
-His knife is gone?

918
00:39:07,144 --> 00:39:09,380
-He had his knife before.
-They can help him look for his knife.

919
00:39:09,447 --> 00:39:10,481
You can use this.

920
00:39:11,048 --> 00:39:12,750
HE URGENTLY PICKS UP
HIS SPARE KNIFE

921
00:39:12,817 --> 00:39:13,884
You can use this.

922
00:39:13,951 --> 00:39:15,686
I have it here. Sorry.

923
00:39:15,753 --> 00:39:18,356
Jong-won lets him borrow his knife!

924
00:39:18,422 --> 00:39:19,423
What a kind heart!

925
00:39:22,059 --> 00:39:24,228
-"A kind heart"?
-He's driving me nuts.

926
00:39:24,795 --> 00:39:26,530
AN EXQUISITE COMMENT

927
00:39:26,597 --> 00:39:28,165
"A kind heart"?

928
00:39:28,232 --> 00:39:31,635
They can't fight if he loses his knife.

929
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:32,770
I was surprised.

930
00:39:32,837 --> 00:39:36,073
But Hyun-suk
doesn't take the knife from Jong-won.

931
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:37,908
"Take it back. I don't need it."

932
00:39:37,975 --> 00:39:40,077
There's a bit
of a psychological war going on.

933
00:39:40,144 --> 00:39:41,946
But he used his knife. Where did it go?

934
00:39:42,012 --> 00:39:44,615
HIS KNIFE HAS ALWAYS BEEN HERE

935
00:39:44,682 --> 00:39:48,619
Chef Hyun-suk is cutting the dough

936
00:39:48,686 --> 00:39:51,021
-into pasta noodles.
-It hasn't been five minutes.

937
00:39:51,088 --> 00:39:53,324
It hasn't been five minutes yet.

938
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:56,293
It's so amazing to see this in real life.

939
00:39:56,861 --> 00:39:58,963
SON JONG-WON FINISHES
WORKING ON THE AVOCADO

940
00:39:59,597 --> 00:40:03,033
He cut the avocado into thin slices.

941
00:40:03,801 --> 00:40:06,303
The insides are quite soft.

942
00:40:07,772 --> 00:40:11,575
4. SMEAR OLIVE OIL AND LIME JUICE
ON PLASTIC WRAP

943
00:40:11,642 --> 00:40:13,277
THEN PUT AVOCADO ON TOP

944
00:40:14,512 --> 00:40:17,281
HOW WILL HE USE THIS?

945
00:40:17,348 --> 00:40:20,885
-Chef Jong-won gets meat. What's the cut?
-He picked up meat.

946
00:40:20,951 --> 00:40:22,186
I'll use tenderloin.

947
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:25,623
-Tenderloin.
-He's using tenderloin.

948
00:40:25,689 --> 00:40:29,026
You're using tenderloin,
yet you won't use any heat?

949
00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:32,830
Tenderloin doesn't have lots of fat,
so it's suitable to make beef tartare.

950
00:40:32,897 --> 00:40:36,033
-Just like Korean-style beef tartare.
-That's right.

951
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,769
5. CHOP BEEF TENDERLOIN FINELY
AND COOL ON ICE

952
00:40:39,670 --> 00:40:41,305
HE BEGINS TO CHOP PICKLED RADISH

