1480
01:04:32,869 --> 01:04:34,403
-That was…
-So?

1481
01:04:34,470 --> 01:04:35,872
Are you in politics now?

1482
01:04:35,938 --> 01:04:37,773
SHOW-OFF PARTY, NUMBER 95,
KWON SUNG-JUN

1483
01:04:37,840 --> 01:04:40,576
You've become quite confident
with Hyun-suk behind you.

1484
01:04:40,643 --> 01:04:41,944
I'm a slow starter.

1485
01:04:42,011 --> 01:04:44,614
I didn't have a great beginning,
but I won against Chef Edward,

1486
01:04:44,680 --> 01:04:48,451
so now I came to challenge myself
against the boss, Chef Yeon-bok.

1487
01:04:49,785 --> 01:04:52,421
-I see.
-He's so confident.

1488
01:04:52,488 --> 01:04:55,691
He's the winner of <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

1489
01:04:55,758 --> 01:04:58,861
so I've been wondering
when I'll get to fight him.

1490
01:04:59,829 --> 01:05:04,634
But the order is for a spicy dish,
so Chef Yeon-bok must have an advantage.

1491
01:05:04,700 --> 01:05:05,902
There are

1492
01:05:05,968 --> 01:05:08,237
all kinds of spicy dishes
in Chinese cuisine.

1493
01:05:08,304 --> 01:05:11,807
<i>-There are many spicy dishes in Sichuan.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

1494
01:05:11,874 --> 01:05:14,844
I also went around that area
to study the local cuisine,

1495
01:05:14,911 --> 01:05:16,545
so I know those dishes very well.

1496
01:05:16,612 --> 01:05:19,849
I probably have an advantage
when it comes to spicy food.

1497
01:05:21,384 --> 01:05:23,986
-I'll make a deliciously spicy dish.
-I see.

1498
01:05:24,053 --> 01:05:26,322
Italy Matfia.

1499
01:05:26,389 --> 01:05:29,625
-Are you sure you're okay with spicy food?
-Italy Matfia?

1500
01:05:29,692 --> 01:05:30,893
-Napoli Matfia.
-Napoli Matfia.

1501
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:32,995
OH, MY

1502
01:05:34,063 --> 01:05:35,898
You need something spicy to wake you.

1503
01:05:35,965 --> 01:05:38,868
-That's the real Mafia!
-What's with you?

1504
01:05:38,935 --> 01:05:41,504
-Please do not misunderstand.
-Napoli Matfia.

1505
01:05:41,570 --> 01:05:43,806
There are no spicy dishes
in Italian cuisine.

1506
01:05:43,873 --> 01:05:46,142
-I see.
-They rarely eat spicy dishes.

1507
01:05:46,208 --> 01:05:49,645
That's why I want to fight him
with a different kind of cuisine.

1508
01:05:50,212 --> 01:05:52,581
Do you also have trouble with spicy food?

1509
01:05:52,648 --> 01:05:54,283
Actually, I don't eat

1510
01:05:54,350 --> 01:05:56,118
anything spicy.

1511
01:05:56,185 --> 01:05:57,186
You can't take spicy food.

1512
01:05:57,253 --> 01:06:00,623
I wouldn't say that.
I just want to protect my palate.

1513
01:06:00,690 --> 01:06:03,259
-Because your tongue is valuable.
-Of course.

1514
01:06:03,326 --> 01:06:05,895
-That means you can't take spicy food.
-I don't eat it at all.

1515
01:06:05,962 --> 01:06:07,430
Nam-no turns his head.

1516
01:06:07,496 --> 01:06:10,766
-I can't listen to this anymore.
-He can't handle it.

1517
01:06:10,833 --> 01:06:14,971
You'll have to taste the spicy food
as you cook later. Will you be okay?

1518
01:06:15,037 --> 01:06:17,873
That's why I prepared some milk.

1519
01:06:19,041 --> 01:06:21,477
-That wasn't for cooking.
-I see.

1520
01:06:21,544 --> 01:06:24,880
He wants to drink it
if his dish tastes too spicy.

1521
01:06:24,947 --> 01:06:27,817
I probably can't finish cooking
without this.

1522
01:06:27,883 --> 01:06:29,051
I see.

1523
01:06:29,885 --> 01:06:33,956
CHEF YEON-BOK'S INGREDIENTS:
CHICKEN POWDER, BRISKET, LAO GAN MA

1524
01:06:34,023 --> 01:06:38,094
BUCKWHEAT NOODLES, PICKLED RADISH,
THAI CHILI, SICHUAN PEPPER, AND MORE

1525
01:06:38,160 --> 01:06:39,829
I prepared a dish called

1526
01:06:39,895 --> 01:06:41,330
Atomic Bok.

1527
01:06:41,397 --> 01:06:45,134
-Atomic Bok?
-Atomic Bok? That sounds strong.

1528
01:06:45,201 --> 01:06:48,571
-Atomic Bok, using his name.
-That's a tough name.

1529
01:06:48,637 --> 01:06:52,041
When it comes to spicy Chinese cuisine,
it's spicy jjamppong, seafood noodles.

1530
01:06:52,108 --> 01:06:55,244
<i>Think of a bowl of jjamppong</i>
<i>that makes you sweat like a pig.</i>

1531
01:06:55,311 --> 01:06:59,448
I want to let him eat that
and get drenched in sweat.

1532
01:06:59,515 --> 01:07:04,286
I'll also let him have a taste
of spicy Chinese-style steak.

1533
01:07:04,353 --> 01:07:05,421
Chinese-style steak.

1534
01:07:05,488 --> 01:07:10,192
I'll present an atomically spicy dish.

1535
01:07:10,259 --> 01:07:12,461
FLUTTERING HANDS

1536
01:07:13,195 --> 01:07:15,131
CHEF SUNG-JUN'S INGREDIENTS:
GHOST PEPPER SAUCE, RAW MOZZARELLA

1537
01:07:15,197 --> 01:07:17,466
CHILI PEPPER BALSAMIC, BEEF TENDERLOIN,
THAI CHILI, OYSTER SAUCE, AND MORE

1538
01:07:17,533 --> 01:07:19,668
The dish I prepared is

1539
01:07:19,735 --> 01:07:21,370
Sichuan Matfia.

1540
01:07:21,437 --> 01:07:25,341
-Sichuan?
-Sichuan, not Napoli?

1541
01:07:25,408 --> 01:07:28,310
-Are you making Chinese cuisine?
-Not Napoli?

1542
01:07:28,377 --> 01:07:29,545
-You're going to Sichuan?
-Sichuan.

1543
01:07:29,612 --> 01:07:33,582
I want to challenge Chef Yeon-bok
by making Chinese cuisine.

1544
01:07:33,649 --> 01:07:35,017
-My gosh.
-Goodness.

1545
01:07:35,084 --> 01:07:37,620
I actually am a certified Chinese chef.

1546
01:07:37,686 --> 01:07:41,357
I'm highly interested in Chinese cuisine,
and I personally love it too.

1547
01:07:41,424 --> 01:07:44,660
I was also greatly inspired
by Chef Yeon-bok's dishes

1548
01:07:44,727 --> 01:07:46,295
through my time on the show.

1549
01:07:46,362 --> 01:07:48,230
I want to share those inspirations.

1550
01:07:48,297 --> 01:07:50,566
I'm going to make mala beef.

1551
01:07:50,633 --> 01:07:52,201
-Mala beef.
-I'll use mala,

1552
01:07:52,268 --> 01:07:54,570
red pepper oil, and beef.

1553
01:07:54,637 --> 01:07:58,074
In Sicily, there's a unique way
of consuming couscous

1554
01:07:58,140 --> 01:08:00,309
so I want to show you that too.

1555
01:08:00,376 --> 01:08:02,411
There's one more key point.

1556
01:08:02,478 --> 01:08:05,448
I'm going to make
European-style zha cai as well.

1557
01:08:05,514 --> 01:08:06,849
European-style zha cai?

1558
01:08:06,916 --> 01:08:11,454
I'll serve some refreshing salad that
includes mozzarella, like Caprese salad.

1559
01:08:11,520 --> 01:08:13,656
You can feel refreshed
as you eat the spicy dishes.

1560
01:08:13,722 --> 01:08:17,126
Matfia now goes all the way to Sichuan.

1561
01:08:17,193 --> 01:08:19,862
I wonder if he'll succeed today.

1562
01:08:19,929 --> 01:08:22,465
And now, let us begin

1563
01:08:22,531 --> 01:08:26,535
round "I won't cry even if it's spicy"
with Keun-suk's ingredients.

1564
01:08:26,602 --> 01:08:30,806
The youngest chef is here to get spicy
with the eldest chef on the show,

1565
01:08:30,873 --> 01:08:32,942
it's Chef Kwon Sung-jun.

1566
01:08:33,008 --> 01:08:36,912
But the eldest chef is ready to give him
a spicy blow and make him cry.

1567
01:08:36,979 --> 01:08:38,781
He's up against Chef Lee Yeon-bok.

1568
01:08:38,848 --> 01:08:43,052
Which one of them will satisfy
Keun-suk's spicy needs?

1569
01:08:43,118 --> 01:08:47,523
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1570
01:08:48,657 --> 01:08:50,092
Begin!

1571
01:08:50,159 --> 01:08:51,560
CHINESE FUSION VS AUTHENTIC CHINESE

1572
01:08:51,627 --> 01:08:53,095
INTRIGUED

1573
01:08:53,762 --> 01:08:56,866
A fight between 1959 and 1995.

1574
01:08:57,900 --> 01:08:59,935
-Those are…
-Sichuan pepper.

1575
01:09:00,002 --> 01:09:02,571
Chef Yeon-bok is grinding Sichuan pepper.

1576
01:09:03,405 --> 01:09:06,609
Jjamppong drives you crazy
if it's too spicy.

1577
01:09:06,675 --> 01:09:08,744
Spicy jjamppong can make you faint.

1578
01:09:08,811 --> 01:09:09,845
It's good, though.

1579
01:09:09,912 --> 01:09:11,347
That pepper isn't just spicy.

1580
01:09:11,413 --> 01:09:13,516
It's spicy and numbing.

1581
01:09:13,582 --> 01:09:17,686
Sichuan pepper is
what gives the spiciness to mala.

1582
01:09:17,753 --> 01:09:20,523
Keun-suk's tongue
doesn't budge with spiciness,

1583
01:09:20,589 --> 01:09:22,825
so he's adding a few other weapons.

1584
01:09:22,892 --> 01:09:25,561
Chef Sung-jun is
up against Master Yeon-bok.

1585
01:09:26,495 --> 01:09:28,631
He's stir-frying minced garlic.

1586
01:09:28,697 --> 01:09:30,366
1. STIR-FRY MINCED GARLIC
AND GINGER IN OLIVE OIL

1587
01:09:31,734 --> 01:09:35,371
I think Chef Sung-jun is
using a Chinese kitchen knife.

1588
01:09:35,437 --> 01:09:36,772
Is that yours?

1589
01:09:36,839 --> 01:09:38,407
I borrowed it from Poong.

1590
01:09:40,209 --> 01:09:43,145
Sung-jun challenges his opponent
with a real Chinese dish.

1591
01:09:43,212 --> 01:09:44,313
My gosh.

1592
01:09:44,380 --> 01:09:45,948
YOU BROUGHT WHAT?

1593
01:09:46,015 --> 01:09:47,750
THUD!

1594
01:09:48,284 --> 01:09:49,285
Whoa!

1595
01:09:49,351 --> 01:09:51,687
He's chopping garlic cloves!

1596
01:09:51,754 --> 01:09:54,957
That's what I'm talking about.
That's Chinese cuisine.

1597
01:09:55,024 --> 01:09:57,026
That's how you use
a Chinese kitchen knife.

1598
01:09:57,092 --> 01:09:58,394
CHOPPING GREEN ONION
IN 5 SECONDS

1599
01:09:58,460 --> 01:09:59,461
6 SECONDS

1600
01:09:59,528 --> 01:10:00,529
7 SECONDS

1601
01:10:00,596 --> 01:10:01,597
8 SECONDS

1602
01:10:01,664 --> 01:10:04,033
HE FINISHES CHOPPING
IN 8 SECONDS!

1603
01:10:04,967 --> 01:10:05,968
My gosh.

1604
01:10:06,035 --> 01:10:07,236
HMPH!

1605
01:10:07,303 --> 01:10:08,304
CHOPPING GREEN ONION IN 1 SECOND

1606
01:10:08,370 --> 01:10:09,371
2 SECONDS, IF IT'S LONGWISE!

1607
01:10:09,438 --> 01:10:10,439
3 SECONDS

1608
01:10:10,506 --> 01:10:12,474
ONLY 3 SECONDS!

1609
01:10:14,410 --> 01:10:15,778
I love that sound.

1610
01:10:16,879 --> 01:10:18,380
THANK YOU FOR THE LESSON!

1611
01:10:18,447 --> 01:10:20,916
He's good with a Chinese kitchen knife.

1612
01:10:20,983 --> 01:10:22,017
Gosh, my knife…

1613
01:10:23,118 --> 01:10:25,688
SUNG-JUN IS ALSO GOOD
AT USING A CHINESE KITCHEN KNIFE

1614
01:10:26,755 --> 01:10:28,290
WHAT'S SUNG-JUN'S
FIRST SPICY FLAVOR?

1615
01:10:28,958 --> 01:10:30,259
What's that?

1616
01:10:30,326 --> 01:10:33,162
-It's the chili crab sauce.
-The chili crab.

1617
01:10:33,229 --> 01:10:36,198
The chili crab sauce
he bought and didn't eat.

1618
01:10:36,265 --> 01:10:37,666
He didn't want it the next day.

1619
01:10:37,733 --> 01:10:39,335
WHAT'S THE NEXT SPICY FLAVOR?

1620
01:10:40,903 --> 01:10:42,905
Is he using Thai chili?

1621
01:10:42,972 --> 01:10:45,307
-Yes, Thai chili.
-Those were spicy.

1622
01:10:45,374 --> 01:10:47,243
He's adding Cheongyang pepper
and Thai chili.

1623
01:10:47,309 --> 01:10:51,013
-It's spicy.
-Things are already smelling spicy.

1624
01:10:51,080 --> 01:10:53,282
I'm starting to get excited.

1625
01:10:53,349 --> 01:10:56,118
This studio now feels like
it's filled with tear gas.

1626
01:10:56,185 --> 01:10:58,420
-My eyes are starting to hurt.
-Yes.

1627
01:10:58,487 --> 01:11:00,122
I think I'm about to sneeze.

1628
01:11:00,189 --> 01:11:04,493
Once you heat up
or stir-fry spicy flavors in oil,

1629
01:11:04,560 --> 01:11:06,028
it'll spread all over the studio.

1630
01:11:06,095 --> 01:11:08,230
-I'm worried.
-Right?

1631
01:11:09,665 --> 01:11:11,200
WHAT'S THE NEXT SPICY PLAYER?

1632
01:11:11,767 --> 01:11:12,768
LAO GAN MA

1633
01:11:12,835 --> 01:11:15,204
It'll be advantageous
to end this round first too.

1634
01:11:15,271 --> 01:11:17,039
They're both spicy,
so if the first one is spicy,

1635
01:11:17,106 --> 01:11:19,508
-the second will feel similar.
-That's right.

1636
01:11:19,575 --> 01:11:21,543
Sung-jun may cut in line again.

1637
01:11:22,678 --> 01:11:25,748
<i>He slammed the bell</i>
<i>after eyeing the timing.</i>

1638
01:11:25,814 --> 01:11:28,183
How will Chef Yeon-bok stop him?

1639
01:11:28,250 --> 01:11:30,319
WILL THE CHEF'S EXPERIENCE
OVERTAKE HIM?

1640
01:11:30,953 --> 01:11:32,187
LEE YEON-BOK SEASONS
CHUCK EYE ROLL

1641
01:11:32,254 --> 01:11:34,256
-The beef.
-He's seasoning the beef.

1642
01:11:34,323 --> 01:11:37,493
He's covering it with starch and eggs.

1643
01:11:37,559 --> 01:11:40,796
That's the basic seasoning
often used in Chinese cuisine.

1644
01:11:40,863 --> 01:11:43,098
2. ADD AND MIX SOY SAUCE, STARCH,
AND EGG WITH CHUCK EYE ROLL

1645
01:11:44,333 --> 01:11:46,969
Two minutes have passed already.

1646
01:11:47,036 --> 01:11:48,270
-Green onion oil?
-Two minutes.

1647
01:11:48,337 --> 01:11:50,406
-Are you making green onion oil?
-No.

1648
01:11:50,472 --> 01:11:52,308
I'm going to parboil the meat in oil.

1649
01:11:52,374 --> 01:11:54,209
-You'll parboil meat in oil?
-Yes, I will.

1650
01:11:54,276 --> 01:11:55,744
I wanted to add some aroma of green onion.

1651
01:11:55,811 --> 01:11:57,313
PARBOILING MEAT IN OIL
KEEPS IT SOFT AND MOIST

1652
01:11:57,379 --> 01:11:59,548
Chef Sung-jun is also using beef.

1653
01:11:59,615 --> 01:12:03,185
-He also put in egg whites.
-He did.

1654
01:12:03,252 --> 01:12:05,487
-Him too.
-It's pretty similar.

1655
01:12:05,554 --> 01:12:06,588
And starch.

1656
01:12:06,655 --> 01:12:08,891
That was the same too.
That's the Chinese style.

1657
01:12:08,957 --> 01:12:11,560
-They're the same.
