I give up now.

1893
01:21:52,207 --> 01:21:54,175
-Ji-won!
-The master of taste!

1894
01:21:54,242 --> 01:21:56,478
-The master of taste!
-The master of taste!

1895
01:21:56,544 --> 01:21:58,647
Now, the master of taste is here!

1896
01:21:59,848 --> 01:22:04,286
-It's one last time.
-Taste it one last time.

1897
01:22:04,352 --> 01:22:06,221
10. SCOOP OUT
COOKED BUCKWHEAT NOODLES

1898
01:22:06,288 --> 01:22:07,489
AND WASH IT IN COLD WATER

1899
01:22:07,555 --> 01:22:09,491
You need this spoon now, Master of Taste.

1900
01:22:09,557 --> 01:22:12,027
Is it atomic? Or has it not gone off yet?

1901
01:22:12,761 --> 01:22:14,562
HER THIRD TASTE OF THE SOUP

1902
01:22:14,629 --> 01:22:16,865
Now, how's the soup?

1903
01:22:16,932 --> 01:22:18,967
-It's her third try!
-The soup!

1904
01:22:19,034 --> 01:22:22,404
Is it atomic?

1905
01:22:23,071 --> 01:22:24,873
-It's an atomic bomb!
-It's an atomic bomb!

1906
01:22:26,308 --> 01:22:28,176
-It's an atomic bomb!
-It's an atomic bomb!

1907
01:22:28,243 --> 01:22:31,646
EVERYONE CHEERS

1908
01:22:31,713 --> 01:22:33,982
-He finally did it.
-It's really spicy.

1909
01:22:34,049 --> 01:22:37,752
-You don't have much time.
-You have a minute!

1910
01:22:38,753 --> 01:22:40,588
-You don't have much time.
-It looks good.

1911
01:22:42,891 --> 01:22:45,593
THE PRESSURE IS GONE,
AND HE CHOPS JOYFULLY

1912
01:22:45,660 --> 01:22:48,196
12. CHOP THE WHITES OF THE GREEN
ONION AND WASH IN COLD WATER

1913
01:22:48,263 --> 01:22:50,165
-What are you adding?
-Red pepper oil.

1914
01:22:50,231 --> 01:22:52,300
He's adding more red medicine on top.

1915
01:22:52,367 --> 01:22:54,336
What did you just add?

1916
01:22:54,402 --> 01:22:55,904
-Red pepper oil.
-Red pepper oil.

1917
01:22:55,971 --> 01:22:58,340
Throw in capsaicin.

1918
01:22:58,406 --> 01:22:59,441
Forty seconds.

1919
01:23:02,043 --> 01:23:04,379
-Mantecare.
-Enough with the mantecare!

1920
01:23:05,113 --> 01:23:07,549
HABITUAL MANTECARE

1921
01:23:07,615 --> 01:23:09,150
The couscous is ready.

1922
01:23:09,217 --> 01:23:10,919
THE CHILI COUSCOUS
IS SERVED FIRST!

1923
01:23:10,986 --> 01:23:12,654
It's important to finish first.

1924
01:23:12,721 --> 01:23:15,957
-You have 26 seconds left.
-It's more advantageous to end first.

1925
01:23:16,024 --> 01:23:19,194
-Okay. You have 20 seconds.
-You have 20 seconds!

1926
01:23:19,260 --> 01:23:20,395
The last 20 seconds!

1927
01:23:20,462 --> 01:23:22,897
-You have twenty seconds!
-Twenty seconds!

1928
01:23:22,964 --> 01:23:24,132
Twenty seconds!

1929
01:23:24,699 --> 01:23:26,134
THE STUDIO
IS GETTING CBR TRAINING

1930
01:23:26,201 --> 01:23:28,837
Chef Yeon-bok isn't done yet!

1931
01:23:28,903 --> 01:23:30,438
The jjamppong!

1932
01:23:30,505 --> 01:23:32,173
-It's going in the dish!
-Ten seconds!

1933
01:23:33,441 --> 01:23:35,643
-Ten seconds!
-Press the bell now!

1934
01:23:35,710 --> 01:23:37,879
-Ten seconds!
-Press the bell now!

1935
01:23:37,946 --> 01:23:38,947
Nine!

1936
01:23:40,081 --> 01:23:41,082
Nine!

1937
01:23:42,384 --> 01:23:43,651
Nine!

1938
01:23:43,718 --> 01:23:45,053
THE BELL FLIES OFF

1939
01:23:45,687 --> 01:23:46,755
SAVE THE FOOD FIRST

1940
01:23:46,821 --> 01:23:48,156
It went through the crack.

1941
01:23:48,223 --> 01:23:50,525
Who pressed the bell first?
Was it Chef Yeon-bok?

1942
01:23:50,592 --> 01:23:54,963
-Let us do an instant replay.
-Instant replay.

1943
01:23:55,030 --> 01:23:57,699
-It was the same time, so let's check.
-They did.

1944
01:23:57,766 --> 01:24:01,202
<i>Whose hand reached the bell first?</i>

1945
01:24:05,774 --> 01:24:09,477
KWON SUNG-JUN GOT TO IT FIRST

1946
01:24:10,245 --> 01:24:14,716
Chef Sung-jun couldn't hit the bell,
but pushed it away instead.

1947
01:24:14,783 --> 01:24:16,351
I wanted to hit it in a haste,

1948
01:24:16,418 --> 01:24:18,086
then it ended up sliding out.

1949
01:24:18,153 --> 01:24:20,255
What should we do?

1950
01:24:20,321 --> 01:24:23,158
Chef Yeon-bok made noodles,

1951
01:24:23,224 --> 01:24:24,526
so he should go first.

1952
01:24:24,592 --> 01:24:26,494
-Will you let him go first? Okay.
-Yes.

1953
01:24:26,561 --> 01:24:30,031
Let us begin with Chef Yeon-bok's dish.

1954
01:24:30,098 --> 01:24:33,301
YEON-BOK'S SPECIALTY, JJAMPPONG

1955
01:24:33,902 --> 01:24:37,172
WITH SPICY AND NUMBING
CHINESE-STYLE STEAK

1956
01:24:37,806 --> 01:24:43,011
CHEF LEE YEON-BOK'S ATOMIC BOK

1957
01:24:43,078 --> 01:24:44,479
I'll try the steak first.

1958
01:24:44,546 --> 01:24:46,614
That dish.

1959
01:24:46,681 --> 01:24:49,017
-It looks good.
-It looks so red that it's dark.

1960
01:24:49,084 --> 01:24:50,652
-It'll sting.
-It's spicy.

1961
01:24:50,718 --> 01:24:51,719
EYES SHUT

1962
01:24:51,786 --> 01:24:52,921
Will he be okay?

1963
01:24:52,987 --> 01:24:55,857
HOW SPICY IS IT?

1964
01:24:56,991 --> 01:25:01,229
The steak was covered in spicy sauce.

1965
01:25:03,064 --> 01:25:04,632
Gosh. Hey.

1966
01:25:04,699 --> 01:25:07,302
-Huh?
-He doesn't even frown.

1967
01:25:07,368 --> 01:25:09,637
-I heard something crunchy.
-Was there a bone?

1968
01:25:11,806 --> 01:25:13,007
A bone? Why?

1969
01:25:14,342 --> 01:25:16,578
Isn't it spicy? Huh?

1970
01:25:16,644 --> 01:25:18,146
Wait, the cracking sound.

1971
01:25:18,213 --> 01:25:19,214
It's probably Sichuan pepper.

1972
01:25:19,280 --> 01:25:22,650
-It must be Sichuan pepper.
-He put Sichuan pepper in there.

1973
01:25:22,717 --> 01:25:24,419
-I didn't know it popped.
-Is it okay?

1974
01:25:25,420 --> 01:25:26,955
Isn't it spicy?

1975
01:25:27,021 --> 01:25:28,289
ACHOO

1976
01:25:28,356 --> 01:25:30,191
Our cameraman is coughing.

1977
01:25:31,025 --> 01:25:32,427
EVERYONE IS COUGHING

1978
01:25:32,494 --> 01:25:35,029
You can't really see them,

1979
01:25:35,096 --> 01:25:37,899
but the camera crew are
all coughing and whatnot.

1980
01:25:37,966 --> 01:25:40,068
This smoke won't leave the studio.

1981
01:25:40,135 --> 01:25:43,171
-Everyone feels the spices.
-This has never happened.

1982
01:25:43,238 --> 01:25:45,273
What struck me first wasn't the spiciness

1983
01:25:45,340 --> 01:25:47,108
but how aromatic it is.

1984
01:25:47,175 --> 01:25:49,644
The aroma just engulfs my nose.

1985
01:25:49,711 --> 01:25:52,213
It doesn't taste unbearably spicy.

1986
01:25:52,280 --> 01:25:53,848
It's a bit spicy,

1987
01:25:53,915 --> 01:25:56,618
and I didn't hate
how I could chew on Sichuan pepper.

1988
01:25:56,684 --> 01:25:59,921
I liked how it tasted even stronger.

1989
01:25:59,988 --> 01:26:02,524
It added a kick in the mouth.

1990
01:26:02,590 --> 01:26:05,226
-It smells good.
-It's not as spicy as it looks.

1991
01:26:05,293 --> 01:26:06,928
-Really?
-I can't believe it.

1992
01:26:06,995 --> 01:26:09,063
How spicy do you take your food?

1993
01:26:09,130 --> 01:26:10,431
This isn't spicy at all.

1994
01:26:10,498 --> 01:26:12,000
-What about jjamppong?
-There's jjamppong.

1995
01:26:12,066 --> 01:26:13,701
-Let me try it.
-Here's jjamppong.

1996
01:26:13,768 --> 01:26:15,803
-The jjamppong.
-That should be very spicy.

1997
01:26:16,704 --> 01:26:19,774
HE ADDED CAPSAICIN
AS THE CHERRY ON TOP

1998
01:26:20,375 --> 01:26:22,210
-It's an atomic bomb!
-It's an atomic bomb!

1999
01:26:22,777 --> 01:26:24,579
COME AND HAVE A BITE
OF THIS ATOMIC TASTE

2000
01:26:24,646 --> 01:26:26,848
-The jjamppong.
-That should be very spicy.

2001
01:26:26,915 --> 01:26:28,416
Look at that.

2002
01:26:28,483 --> 01:26:29,817
It's almost like stew.

2003
01:26:30,385 --> 01:26:32,453
THIS JJAMPPONG WILL
STOP HIM FROM SHOWING OFF

2004
01:26:33,321 --> 01:26:34,722
COUGH

2005
01:26:34,789 --> 01:26:36,324
WHAT WILL HAPPEN
TO PRINCE SPICY?

2006
01:26:36,391 --> 01:26:37,425
He tries the soup first.

2007
01:26:40,195 --> 01:26:42,664
Ji-won said she almost fainted.

2008
01:26:43,298 --> 01:26:44,532
OH?

2009
01:26:45,099 --> 01:26:46,367
ANOTHER SIP OF THE SOUP

2010
01:26:46,434 --> 01:26:48,503
-He's sipping the soup.
-I guess it's not spicy enough.

2011
01:26:48,570 --> 01:26:50,271
Whoa.

2012
01:26:50,338 --> 01:26:52,574
Do you feel okay?

2013
01:26:52,640 --> 01:26:54,976
HMPH

2014
01:26:56,044 --> 01:26:57,679
He tried very hard.

2015
01:26:57,745 --> 01:27:00,181
GASP

2016
01:27:00,248 --> 01:27:01,950
-He tried?
-He tried very hard?

2017
01:27:02,717 --> 01:27:04,219
-He tried.
-Even I can feel the spiciness.

2018
01:27:04,285 --> 01:27:07,188
Gosh, she's coughing. Ji-won is done.

2019
01:27:09,657 --> 01:27:11,926
It feels spicy just to see him eat.

2020
01:27:11,993 --> 01:27:15,997
-Why do you eat such spicy food?
-I wonder.

2021
01:27:16,064 --> 01:27:18,032
His eyes are red.

2022
01:27:19,000 --> 01:27:21,703
EVEN THE ATOMIC TASTE
ISN'T ENOUGH FOR HIM?

2023
01:27:27,508 --> 01:27:28,509
-Oh, no.
-Is it spicy?

2024
01:27:28,576 --> 01:27:29,844
-It's spicy!
-The spiciness hit him!

2025
01:27:29,911 --> 01:27:31,346
-Oh, no.
-Is it spicy?

2026
01:27:31,412 --> 01:27:34,215
-It's spicy! It hit him!
-The spiciness hit him!

2027
01:27:34,282 --> 01:27:35,984
-It hit him.
-Are you crying?

2028
01:27:36,050 --> 01:27:37,051
His eyes are in tears.

2029
01:27:37,118 --> 01:27:40,655
No, my late grandfather
used to love jjamppong so much.

2030
01:27:40,722 --> 01:27:43,057
-That can happen.
-He can remember.

2031
01:27:43,124 --> 01:27:45,059
-We have nothing to say to that.
-That can make you cry.

2032
01:27:45,126 --> 01:27:47,328
-That can happen.
-It can.

2033
01:27:47,395 --> 01:27:48,396
Mmm.

2034
01:27:50,131 --> 01:27:52,900
-It's so good.
-It's so good!

2035
01:27:52,967 --> 01:27:56,104
And the noodles too.
I honestly love flour so much,

2036
01:27:56,170 --> 01:27:58,306
but I try to stay away from it.

2037
01:27:58,373 --> 01:28:01,109
The buckwheat noodles were
made 100% with buckwheat.

2038
01:28:01,175 --> 01:28:02,910
So there's no pressure when I eat this.

2039
01:28:02,977 --> 01:28:04,846
HE'LL RELAX AND START EATING

2040
01:28:04,912 --> 01:28:07,115
SLURPING

2041
01:28:08,182 --> 01:28:10,752
HE EATS
AND EATS AGAIN

2042
01:28:12,086 --> 01:28:13,721
IT'S HARD FOR THE VIEWERS
TO WATCH THE MUKBANG

2043
01:28:13,788 --> 01:28:16,157
It's a wonder.

2044
01:28:16,224 --> 01:28:17,392
I can't watch this.

2045
01:28:17,992 --> 01:28:20,161
-But it looks so good.
-Yes.

2046
01:28:20,228 --> 01:28:23,231
Some people eat spicy food
with a frown, looking stressed out.

2047
01:28:23,298 --> 01:28:25,933
But he doesn't. He looks relaxed.

2048
01:28:26,000 --> 01:28:28,603
-My stress melted by watching him.
-Really.

2049
01:28:28,670 --> 01:28:32,106
Everyone else is frowning, but he's happy.

2050
01:28:32,173 --> 01:28:35,176
Watching him enjoy such spicy food

2051
01:28:35,243 --> 01:28:37,779
kind of makes my stress melt away too.

2052
01:28:37,845 --> 01:28:39,580
-You're living vicariously.
-I am.

2053
01:28:39,647 --> 01:28:42,884
-It's so pleasantly spicy.
-It's that spicy.

2054
01:28:42,950 --> 01:28:45,787
I think this is the kind of taste
that people call spicy.

2055
01:28:45,853 --> 01:28:47,121
But it feels great.

2056
01:28:47,188 --> 01:28:48,723
HE'S AMAZING

2057
01:28:48,790 --> 01:28:49,791
He's something.

2058
01:28:49,857 --> 01:28:54,395
-Oh, no. What will he do now?
-He's good with spicy food.

2059
01:28:54,462 --> 01:28:57,565
Next, Chef Sung-jun's Sichuan Matfia.

2060
01:28:57,632 --> 01:28:59,701
SPICY MALA BEEF
AND CHILI COUSCOUS

2061
01:29:01,269 --> 01:29:04,539
EUROPEAN-STYLE ZHA CAI
TO PROTECT(?) HIS STOMACH

2062
01:29:05,440 --> 01:29:08,643
CHEF KWON SUNG-JUN'S
SICHUAN MATFIA

2063
01:29:09,210 --> 01:29:10,411
DAZED

2064
01:29:10,478 --> 01:29:13,681
Chef Sung-jun is almost knocked out.

2065
01:29:13,748 --> 01:29:15,083
He looks like he was at a sauna.

2066
01:29:15,149 --> 01:29:16,551
Why is he holding that water bottle?

2067
01:29:16,617 --> 01:29:20,455
He made the most spicy dish
in his opinion.

2068
01:29:20,521 --> 01:29:21,989
I wonder how spicy it is.

2069
01:29:24,859 --> 01:29:27,328
Chef Hyun-suk will have a taste
as the chefs' representative.

2070
01:29:28,229 --> 01:29:30,031
-Of course.
-Me?

2071
01:29:30,098 --> 01:29:32,633
You always sat there and had a taste.

2072
01:29:32,700 --> 01:29:34,102
He'll try it now.

2073
01:29:34,168 --> 01:29:36,571
Chef Sung-jun's Sichuan Matfia.

2074
01:29:37,505 --> 01:29:39,173
Gosh, he's eating that.

2075
01:29:40,708 --> 01:29:42,310
TAKING A BIG BITE
WITHOUT HESITATION

2076
01:29:42,377 --> 01:29:44,846
I wonder what it's like.

2077
01:29:44,912 --> 01:29:47,682
I hope he's okay.

2078
01:29:47,749 --> 01:29:50,084
But he's not sweating yet.

2079
01:29:50,151 --> 01:29:51,586
You're right. He isn't.

2080
01:29:51,652 --> 01:29:54,756
-He should be sweating a lot by now.
-Yes.

2081
01:29:54,822 --> 01:29:56,157
The couscous.

2082
01:29:58,493 --> 01:30:01,929
He should've gone from Naples to Sichuan.

2083
01:30:01,996 --> 01:30:03,231
It must taste special.

2084
01:30:03,297 --> 01:30:04,766
Did he arrive at Sichuan?

2085
01:30:04,832 --> 01:30:07,001
We took a stop there
and visited Singapore.

2086
01:30:07,068 --> 01:30:09,137
-I see.
-You're at Singapore?

2087
01:30:09,203 --> 01:30:11,572
<i>-The chili crab sauce.</i>
<i>-The chili crab sauce.</i>

2088
01:30:11,639 --> 01:30:14,942
<i>-You're right.</i>
<i>-The chili crab sauce.</i>

2089
01:30:15,009 --> 01:30:16,711
Cilantro and the honey butter almond.

2090
01:30:16,778 --> 01:30:20,281
When the taste gets too old,
try the refreshing European zha cai.

2091
01:30:20,348 --> 01:30:21,349
The zha cai.

2092
01:30:21,416 --> 01:30:23,017
-The one with cheese.
-Yes.

2093
01:30:23,084 --> 01:30:26,387
The Italian-style zha cai.
Try it with the cheese.

2094
01:30:26,454 --> 01:30:29,123
Have it with the cheese
and the cabbage in there,

2095
01:30:29,190 --> 01:30:31,125
just like salad or pickled radish.

2096
01:30:31,192 --> 01:30:32,193
Is this spicy too?

2097
01:30:32,260 --> 01:30:35,363
It's a bit spicy,
but it probably isn't spicy for him.

2098
01:30:35,430 --> 01:30:36,964
WHAT'S IT LIKE?

2099
01:30:37,031 --> 01:30:38,199
That looks good.

2100
01:30:39,000 --> 01:30:41,702
The other chefs don't look like

2101
01:30:42,270 --> 01:30:44,539
they're watching someone eat food.

2102
01:30:44,605 --> 01:30:48,776
It's like they're watching someone
perform amazing circus tricks.

2103
01:30:48,843 --> 01:30:51,279
It's like a show
that shows shocking people.

2104
01:30:51,345 --> 01:30:53,047
"How is he like that?"

2105
01:30:53,614 --> 01:30:54,882
EYES OPENED WIDE

2106
01:30:54,949 --> 01:30:56,117
It must be good.

2107
01:30:56,184 --> 01:30:57,552
NODDING

2108
01:30:57,618 --> 01:30:59,086
I'LL NOD TOO

2109
01:30:59,153 --> 01:31:01,923
The tug of war
between these two is perfect.

2110
01:31:01,989 --> 01:31:04,091
If I eat this
when it feels a little spicy,

2111
01:31:04,158 --> 01:31:07,628
-it clears all the spiciness.
-I see.

2112
01:31:07,695 --> 01:31:08,963
It must have great balance.

2113
01:31:09,030 --> 01:31:11,232
If I only had these,
it would've felt too greasy.

2114
01:31:11,299 --> 01:31:13,734
-But sauerkraut tastes sour.
-Yes.

2115
01:31:13,801 --> 01:31:18,306
That adds a refreshing taste
as if it's melting the grease away.

2116
01:31:18,372 --> 01:31:21,843
Then you become encouraged enough
to pick up another piece.

2117
01:31:21,909 --> 01:31:23,177
YUM

2118
01:31:23,244 --> 01:31:25,379
OH, MY GOODNESS

2119
01:31:26,147 --> 01:31:27,381
He doesn't say it's spicy.

2120
01:31:27,448 --> 01:31:28,749
He doesn't say that.

2121
01:31:29,750 --> 01:31:31,452
-Is it not spicy?
-I guess not.

2122
01:31:31,519 --> 01:31:33,154
-It's not spicy.
-It isn't?

2123
01:31:33,221 --> 01:31:34,989
It's good. I love the smell.

2124
01:31:35,556 --> 01:31:37,124
Did you use lao gan ma?

2125
01:31:37,191 --> 01:31:38,326
<i>Yes, I did.</i>

2126
01:31:38,392 --> 01:31:42,663
That adds a punch
of spiciness for the dish.

2127
01:31:42,730 --> 01:31:44,532
Why are you sitting like that?

2128
01:31:44,599 --> 01:31:46,300
-What?
-Your posture.

2129
01:31:46,367 --> 01:31:48,069
It's not like
you're seeing something crazy.

2130
01:31:48,135 --> 01:31:49,904
-It's not that.
-He's just eating food.

2131
01:31:49,971 --> 01:31:51,706
I thought he was cool.

2132
01:31:53,908 --> 01:31:54,909
He's so cool.

2133
01:31:54,976 --> 01:31:57,478
Now, should Chef Hyun-suk
start with a bite?

2134
01:31:57,545 --> 01:31:59,080
-He's right there.
-Yes.

2135
01:31:59,146 --> 01:32:00,748
-Let me have one.
-Try one each.

2136
01:32:00,815 --> 01:32:04,285
Chef Hyun-suk is trying a bite.

2137
01:32:04,352 --> 01:32:05,620
Chef Kang-rok?

2138
01:32:05,686 --> 01:32:08,489
I'm pretty frail…

2139
01:32:08,556 --> 01:32:11,759
-Please don't strain yourself.
-I can't eat that.

2140
01:32:11,826 --> 01:32:13,828
-We welcome volunteers.
-And challengers.

2141
01:32:13,895 --> 01:32:16,831
-Who wants to try? Poong.
-Poong.

2142
01:32:16,898 --> 01:32:18,499
-It's good.
-I don't want it.

2143
01:32:18,566 --> 01:32:20,968
-It must be delicious.
-What about the spiciness?

2144
01:32:21,035 --> 01:32:22,537
The spiciness?

2145
01:32:22,603 --> 01:32:26,674
I'm the type who has trouble
eating that spicy ramyeon.

2146
01:32:26,741 --> 01:32:29,443
But it's spicy enough for me to eat.
It's deliciously spicy.

2147
01:32:29,510 --> 01:32:31,445
-Really?
-It's not crazily spicy.

2148
01:32:31,512 --> 01:32:33,014
-It's really good.
-Yes.

2149
01:32:33,581 --> 01:32:35,516
THE ONES WHO CAN'T EAT
SPICY FOOD GIVE IT A TRY

2150
01:32:40,288 --> 01:32:41,455
ARGH

2151
01:32:41,522 --> 01:32:42,523
ARRRGHH

2152
01:32:43,090 --> 01:32:44,225
MAKING A SCENE

2153
01:32:44,292 --> 01:32:45,993
He's making a scene over there.

2154
01:32:46,060 --> 01:32:47,728
-Stop overreacting!
-The two are

2155
01:32:47,795 --> 01:32:49,230
-almost breakdancing.
-Oh, no.

2156
01:32:49,297 --> 01:32:51,532
-Stop lying.
-Those two.

2157
01:32:51,599 --> 01:32:54,135
-It's not that bad.
-It's not?

2158
01:32:54,201 --> 01:32:57,038
Jong-won and Nam-no are done.

2159
01:32:57,104 --> 01:32:58,573
And this.

2160
01:33:00,641 --> 01:33:01,809
The jjamppong.

2161
01:33:02,543 --> 01:33:04,145
I'm bad with spicy food too,

2162
01:33:04,211 --> 01:33:05,980
but is it because it's delicious?

2163
01:33:06,047 --> 01:33:08,382
I guess the deliciousness
cancels out the spiciness.

2164
01:33:08,449 --> 01:33:11,419
Ji-won tries it once again.

2165
01:33:11,485 --> 01:33:13,020
She's feeling it.

2166
01:33:13,721 --> 01:33:16,524
-It's an atomic bomb.
-It's an atomic bomb.

2167
01:33:16,591 --> 01:33:19,060
It's an atomic bomb.
She just had the jjamppong.

2168
01:33:19,126 --> 01:33:22,663
-It's spicy.
-It's normal for people to sweat.

2169
01:33:22,730 --> 01:33:24,899
It's delicious, but it's too spicy.

2170
01:33:24,966 --> 01:33:26,033
It's an atomic bomb.

2171
01:33:26,100 --> 01:33:30,705
-Why is Chef Kang-rok down without eating?
-What's wrong?

2172
01:33:30,771 --> 01:33:32,440
You look like you had everything.

2173
01:33:32,506 --> 01:33:34,208
Something flew over to me.

2174
01:33:34,275 --> 01:33:36,243
GETTING DIZZY

2175
01:33:38,312 --> 01:33:40,982
Gosh, my head.

2176
01:33:41,048 --> 01:33:43,284
You're finally feeling it.

2177
01:33:43,351 --> 01:33:46,754
Does your head sting and tickle
when you eat spicy food?

2178
01:33:46,821 --> 01:33:47,822
-Yes.
-It happens.

2179
01:33:47,888 --> 01:33:49,490
Is Sam okay?

2180
01:33:49,557 --> 01:33:51,659
-I can handle this.
-You can?

2181
01:33:51,726 --> 01:33:53,127
-It's not too spicy.
-Try the couscous.

2182
01:33:53,194 --> 01:33:55,796
-Try mine.
-Try the couscous this time.

2183
01:33:55,863 --> 01:33:56,964
Do you want to try it?

2184
01:33:59,834 --> 01:34:01,168
Is it good?

2185
01:34:02,036 --> 01:34:03,137
Is it not spicy?

2186
01:34:03,704 --> 01:34:05,039
-It is.
-It is?

2187
01:34:05,106 --> 01:34:06,874
ANOTHER KO

2188
01:34:07,441 --> 01:34:10,211
THE SPICINESS OF SICHUAN MATFIA

2189
01:34:10,277 --> 01:34:11,579
-Sam and Poong.
-He's sweating.

2190
01:34:11,646 --> 01:34:13,514
NEXT,
THE CHALLENGE OF THE SURVIVORS(?)

2191
01:34:14,415 --> 01:34:16,250
Whoa, this is spicy.

2192
01:34:17,585 --> 01:34:18,686
LAUGHING

2193
01:34:18,753 --> 01:34:21,355
My gosh. He said that was spicy.

2194
01:34:21,422 --> 01:34:22,923
I keep feeling it.

2195
01:34:22,990 --> 01:34:25,159
-There's no capsaicin in here either.
-Couscous is currently

2196
01:34:25,226 --> 01:34:27,461
-the most spicy dish.
-Why is this spicy?

2197
01:34:27,528 --> 01:34:29,697
He added Thai chili in it.

2198
01:34:29,764 --> 01:34:31,599
-I see.
-I put in some Thai chili.

2199
01:34:31,666 --> 01:34:33,034
You put it in right away.

2200
01:34:33,100 --> 01:34:34,802
The dishes were all good,

2201
01:34:34,869 --> 01:34:36,637
but this couscous was the most spicy.

2202
01:34:36,704 --> 01:34:39,106
Yes, this was the most spicy.

2203
01:34:39,173 --> 01:34:41,542
-Poong, did you try it? How was it?
-Yes, I tried it all.

2204
01:34:41,609 --> 01:34:44,278
I have a feeling
these weren't spicy enough

2205
01:34:44,345 --> 01:34:47,181
-for Keun-suk.
-Right.

2206
01:34:47,248 --> 01:34:48,983
These are both deliciously spicy.

2207
01:34:49,050 --> 01:34:51,686
They both could've gone further.

2208
01:34:51,752 --> 01:34:53,521
-They stick to a moral code.
-Yes.

2209
01:34:53,587 --> 01:34:56,123
They have to make it humanly edible.

2210
01:34:56,190 --> 01:34:58,626
Keun-suk, the guy
who can take extremely spicy food.

2211
01:34:58,693 --> 01:35:00,494
-This is hard.
-You can consider

2212
01:35:00,561 --> 01:35:03,564
the level of spiciness,
its taste, and more.

2213
01:35:03,631 --> 01:35:05,733
Press one for Lee Yeon-bok,

2214
01:35:05,800 --> 01:35:07,668
and press two for Kwon Sung-jun.

2215
01:35:07,735 --> 01:35:09,837
Please make your decision

2216
01:35:09,904 --> 01:35:11,305
and press it!

2217
01:35:11,372 --> 01:35:14,208
He made his decision.

2218
01:35:14,275 --> 01:35:17,778
A battle between a man born in 1959
and another man born in 1995.

2219
01:35:17,845 --> 01:35:19,580
Let's find out the result.

2220
01:35:19,647 --> 01:35:21,916
-Show us!
-Gosh, this is…

2221
01:35:21,982 --> 01:35:24,552
-Mr. Spicy.
-I won't cry!

2222
01:35:24,618 --> 01:35:28,689
Will Chef Yeon-bok win
and show the class of the veteran?

2223
01:35:28,756 --> 01:35:33,427
Or will Chef Sung-jun win
and open up a new era?

2224
01:35:33,494 --> 01:35:36,197
Who did Keun-suk choose?

2225
01:35:36,263 --> 01:35:38,199
Who will take the star?

2226
01:35:38,265 --> 01:35:42,103
Who made a delicious yet spicy dish?

2227
01:35:42,770 --> 01:35:45,239
-Who did Keun-suk choose?
-Who is it?

2228
01:35:46,040 --> 01:35:47,074
Who is it?

2229
01:35:47,141 --> 01:35:48,809
KWON SUNG-JUN WINS

2230
01:35:48,876 --> 01:35:50,478
CHEF KWON SUNG-JUN'S
SICHUAN MATFIA WINS

2231
01:35:50,544 --> 01:35:54,215
Sung-jun! Sung-jun wins.

2232
01:35:55,816 --> 01:35:59,053
-Whoa.
-I can't believe this.

2233
01:35:59,120 --> 01:36:01,255
It was a difficult decision.

2234
01:36:01,322 --> 01:36:06,193
I was very grateful
for their hard work and delicious dishes.

2235
01:36:06,260 --> 01:36:08,195
But I honestly didn't think
they were spicy.

2236
01:36:08,262 --> 01:36:10,631
So regardless of that,

2237
01:36:10,698 --> 01:36:15,836
I began to wonder which one of them had
a more interesting mix of ingredients

2238
01:36:15,903 --> 01:36:18,706
as they went through my fridge.

2239
01:36:18,773 --> 01:36:21,308
Chef Yeon-bok's dish was

2240
01:36:21,375 --> 01:36:23,911
such authentic Chinese cuisine.

2241
01:36:23,978 --> 01:36:27,915
But Chef Kwon's dish included
my favorite, couscous, too.

2242
01:36:28,649 --> 01:36:30,518
I thought it was easier to approach.

2243
01:36:30,584 --> 01:36:32,219
Their styles were completely different,

2244
01:36:32,286 --> 01:36:34,588
but if I wanted to make one of the dishes,

2245
01:36:34,655 --> 01:36:38,926
-I'll probably want to try his.
-I see.

2246
01:36:38,993 --> 01:36:41,862
Ji-won, you seemed surprised
with the result.

2247
01:36:41,929 --> 01:36:43,798
Was it unexpected?

2248
01:36:43,864 --> 01:36:44,999
No.

2249
01:36:45,065 --> 01:36:48,335
-We're watching everything.
-Stop watching me.

2250
01:36:48,402 --> 01:36:52,173
You didn't seem convinced.
You were like, "Huh?"

2251
01:36:52,239 --> 01:36:53,274
-No.
-What is it?

2252
01:36:53,340 --> 01:36:56,110
Would you have chosen differently?

2253
01:36:56,177 --> 01:36:59,747
I had a taste of his jjamppong, right?

2254
01:36:59,814 --> 01:37:02,750
-It was spicy, yet it was so good.
-It was.

2255
01:37:02,817 --> 01:37:05,653
I really enjoyed this too.

2256
01:37:05,719 --> 01:37:10,457
It looks like we're in a new era now.

2257
01:37:10,524 --> 01:37:13,227
It was such an honor
to stand here and cook

2258
01:37:13,294 --> 01:37:16,497
next to a big master of Chinese cuisine
like him.

2259
01:37:16,564 --> 01:37:20,835
I thought I won by sheer luck
only because the theme was spiciness.

2260
01:37:20,901 --> 01:37:23,671
You won another star
along with Chef Hyun-suk.

2261
01:37:23,737 --> 01:37:25,472
This means <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> is

2262
01:37:25,539 --> 01:37:27,942
now taken over with the Hyun-suk types.

2263
01:37:28,008 --> 01:37:29,977
It's about to become a show-off show.

2264
01:37:30,044 --> 01:37:31,979
Keun-suk, please put the star on him.

2265
01:37:32,813 --> 01:37:35,549
-Chef Sung-jun gets two stars!
-Thank you.

2266
01:37:35,616 --> 01:37:38,619
-A new age has begun.
-Yes, congratulations.

2267
01:37:38,686 --> 01:37:40,955
THE MEN WHO CAPTURED THE WORLD

2268
01:37:41,021 --> 01:37:44,358
Please welcome two world-renowned stars,
j-hope and Heo Sung-tae!

2269
01:37:44,425 --> 01:37:45,659
THE SPECIAL MC

2270
01:37:45,726 --> 01:37:46,727
WELCOME, BTS J-HOPE

2271
01:37:46,794 --> 01:37:49,330
I returned after finishing
my mandatory military service.

2272
01:37:49,396 --> 01:37:51,565
-I was a drill sergeant.
-A drill sergeant?

2273
01:37:51,632 --> 01:37:53,234
The food was delicious.

2274
01:37:53,300 --> 01:37:55,169
They'd serve dishes like <i>mala</i> tteokbokki.

2275
01:37:55,236 --> 01:37:56,570
That suddenly happened?

2276
01:37:56,637 --> 01:37:59,406
She's the most legendary judge
of MasterChef Korea.

2277
01:37:59,473 --> 01:38:02,009
Please welcome Chef Kim Sohyi!

2278
01:38:02,076 --> 01:38:03,544
<i>I'm very glad to be here.</i>

2279
01:38:03,611 --> 01:38:05,512
<i>Thank you for inviting me.</i>

2280
01:38:05,579 --> 01:38:07,848
A DRAMATIC REUNIFICATION
OF A CONTESTANT AND A JUDGE

2281
01:38:07,915 --> 01:38:09,516
What is this? You aren't a kid.

2282
01:38:10,050 --> 01:38:11,318
KANG-ROK'S BIGGEST CRISIS

2283
01:38:11,385 --> 01:38:14,188
<i>I came thinking I had to win a star today.</i>

2284
01:38:14,255 --> 01:38:16,590
-I think I'll lose.
-Nam-no!

2285
01:38:16,657 --> 01:38:18,959
His boldness captured me.

2286
01:38:19,026 --> 01:38:20,427
Wait!

2287
01:38:20,494 --> 01:38:21,795
-Whoa!
-It's too hot.

2288
01:38:21,862 --> 01:38:23,264
How will they finish?

2289
01:38:23,330 --> 01:38:25,332
THE TWO FEARLESS MANIACS(?)
HAVE A COOK-OFF!

2290
01:38:25,399 --> 01:38:26,667
<i>I'm an expert in making tiramisu.</i>

2291
01:38:26,734 --> 01:38:28,235
<i>I'll show you what my dessert is like.</i>

2292
01:38:28,302 --> 01:38:29,737
AN UNIMAGINABLE DESSERT BATTLE!

2293
01:38:29,803 --> 01:38:32,606
-He's doing a performance!
-He's performing!

2294
01:38:32,673 --> 01:38:33,941
Let me serve it for you.

2295
01:38:34,008 --> 01:38:35,576
WE'RE HERE FOR A FULL EXPERIENCE

2296
01:38:35,643 --> 01:38:38,045
What is this?

2297
01:38:38,112 --> 01:38:40,781
<i>He's putting wings on j-hope.</i>

2298
01:38:40,848 --> 01:38:42,516
-How is it?
-Is it on fire?

2299
01:38:42,583 --> 01:38:43,984
He keeps smiling.

2300
01:38:45,319 --> 01:38:47,688
-It's good.
-All right!

2301
01:38:57,298 --> 01:39:02,303
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
